b2d913c4-aae9-4f1b-9d2a-221469a090aa.question: Would a situation of academic misconduct that resulted in a student's exmatriculation impact their application to the AI in Society program at TUM?
b2d913c4-aae9-4f1b-9d2a-221469a090aa.answer: The first step is to check whether the student's previous degree and the AI in Society program at TUM are similar. If they are not similar, the student should be able to apply with no problems. If they are highly similar, the student will likely be declined by TUM.

eb3982c4-5f10-4163-80cf-490dec44d8d1.question: Would a situation of academic misconduct and subsequent exmatriculation impact an application to the AI in Society program at TUM?
eb3982c4-5f10-4163-80cf-490dec44d8d1.answer: If you have finally failed a subject and you have therefore failed your degree, you are exempted from doing the same/similar degree anywhere else in Germany. The first step is to check whether your degree and our degree are similar enough ('fachverwandt'). If they are not similar, you should be able to apply with no problems. If they are highly similar, you will likely be declined by TUM.

9a3d0ce5-3b04-4194-a8e1-3709c52a84eb.question: Is it possible to get a Letter of endorsement (Betreuungszusage) for a scholarship application?
9a3d0ce5-3b04-4194-a8e1-3709c52a84eb.answer: You should reach out to the study program head, Prof. [REDACTED]. She should be able to support you with this if you describe your situation well and that you are a prospective student.

748aef6c-5a36-4913-a08d-9be28ba245bd.question: With my background, may I ask if I would be considered as a candidate for the AI in Society program?

1b5d59b2-a02a-4dd0-a996-04cbc752ec4c.question: What is the format of the aptitude test for M.Sc (AI in Society)?
1b5d59b2-a02a-4dd0-a996-04cbc752ec4c.answer: The format of the aptitude test is closed-book, so there are no additional aids allowed.

170cb794-91d8-4a24-9b72-4d9edeaee686.question: Is it possible to talk to professors or students at TUM to get a deeper understanding of what the 'AI in Society' course is like?
170cb794-91d8-4a24-9b72-4d9edeaee686.answer: Talking to professors or students would need some organizing. However, if you have concrete questions, you can forward them to the email sender.

8dd57b3c-88e0-446e-887c-42a1801d40ec.question: Where can I find more information about the aptitude test and certain modules for the AI in Society program?
8dd57b3c-88e0-446e-887c-42a1801d40ec.answer: Information about the aptitude test and certain modules can be found on the website: https://www.sot.tum.de/sot/studium/ai-in-society/application/

b846846d-5a4c-488e-bd96-a6661d615ba9.question: Is a Bachelor's degree in social sciences, political sciences, economics, law, and psychology, or a related field a strict requirement for the MSc program in AI in Society at TUM?
b846846d-5a4c-488e-bd96-a6661d615ba9.answer: No, it is not a strict requirement. You can apply with any Bachelor's degree.

66edc1ca-78f8-48bf-82e3-c67eff94e078.question: I have already completed a Master's degree. May I list the credits I earned during my master's study?
66edc1ca-78f8-48bf-82e3-c67eff94e078.answer: No, please only list credits from your Bachelor’s degree. We cannot actually take a Master’s degree as basis for another Master’s degree application. It will always be the Bachelor’s degree that is relevant.

6d311958-b22f-4da5-8758-e6300810c179.question: What was the decision on the rest of the cases for recognition in the AI in Society program?
6d311958-b22f-4da5-8758-e6300810c179.answer: The rest of the cases for recognition were unfortunately declined.

7e62c58f-12a2-4606-946c-6cd4f6aefc6c.question: What was the result of the credit recognition application for the AI in Society courses “Foundations of AI and [REDACTED]”, “Introduction to Programming and [REDACTED]” and “Introduction to [REDACTED]”?
7e62c58f-12a2-4606-946c-6cd4f6aefc6c.answer: The credit recognition application for these courses was declined by the examination board.

b8325aa9-b378-481f-8228-a622ac94b3c8.question: What was the result of the credit recognition application for the AI in Society courses “Foundations of AI and [REDACTED]” and “Introduction to Programming and [REDACTED]”?
b8325aa9-b378-481f-8228-a622ac94b3c8.answer: The credit recognition application for the AI in Society courses “Foundations of AI and [REDACTED]” and “Introduction to Programming and [REDACTED]” was declined by the examination board.

84fc4bc9-e2a0-4724-9a99-185f3cb891d3.question: Could you kindly provide the individual scores for my academic performance and the writing test from the first stage of the application process?
84fc4bc9-e2a0-4724-9a99-185f3cb891d3.answer: You had received 18 points based on your grades (academic performance) and 29 points in the written test. This led to 47 points in total, after which you were invited to the interview.

df19cd6f-cb27-4636-ae71-0b18ccda2763.question: Could you share information about the tuition fees or any other costs associated with the program?
df19cd6f-cb27-4636-ae71-0b18ccda2763.answer: The tuition fees per semester for students outside of the EU currently amount to 4000 euros. You can find more information about this here: https://www.tum.de/en/studies/fees/tuition

84174e9a-151a-4cb9-95a7-38ca2bb18c30.question: Would being exmatriculated due to academic misconduct from a previous masters degree at a german university affect the application to the AI in Society program at TUM?
84174e9a-151a-4cb9-95a7-38ca2bb18c30.answer: The first step is to check whether your previous degree and the MSc. AI in Society are similar. If they are not similar, you should be able to apply with no problems. If they are highly similar, you will likely be declined by TUM.

f3033e65-54a5-4b29-96ef-134e6c2aa700.question: Do I need to explicitly apply for scholarships for international students at TUM and if so, where and how can I apply for them?
f3033e65-54a5-4b29-96ef-134e6c2aa700.answer: For all questions regarding scholarships, you should reach out to TUM’s scholarship office. More information can be found on their website.

378d7a2d-e645-4609-bb03-0db6f0f9324b.question: Will it be a problem if my thesis, which is a practical one on AI, only accounts for 12 ECTS credits instead of the recommended 18 in the application requirements?
378d7a2d-e645-4609-bb03-0db6f0f9324b.answer: If you cannot provide at least 18 ECTS worth of practical experience with your application, the application will unfortunately be declined. However, practical experience outside of the university context, for example in the form of work experience, is also counted.

3fed13d7-ff2c-47cb-8057-f7b17a92b0a9.question: Could you provide more insight into the assessment of political and social sciences in the aptitude test?
3fed13d7-ff2c-47cb-8057-f7b17a92b0a9.answer: I can’t give out detailed information about the contents of the test, unfortunately, at least not beyond of what can be found on our website. However, I can tell you that we will not be asking very specific questions (like business law or similar). The test will be multiple choice, so you should be able to recognize the correct answers with general knowledge.

a67cb436-74bb-4b9f-a495-0b5305623a9e.question: Are there any other specific admission criteria I should be aware of or additional steps I might need to take?
a67cb436-74bb-4b9f-a495-0b5305623a9e.answer: All of the relevant admission criteria and procedures can be found on the website: https://www.sot.tum.de/sot/studium/ai-in-society/application/

34038c90-75fc-4bdd-a895-1f113ad647e9.question: Can contributions to open-source software development count towards the project requirements for the MSc. AI in Society program at TUM?

f4b4fe43-c2dc-4732-9580-2bfbc0f3e884.question: Who needs to nominate the applicant for the scholarship?
f4b4fe43-c2dc-4732-9580-2bfbc0f3e884.answer: The applicant needs to be nominated by a professor.

1f9baf22-a70b-4ffd-82c3-76c18bfe3e21.question: How many ECTS is the Project Week worth?

2b115b4d-0e2c-457a-8ac9-6ddcd2cb0d8f.question: Can I apply at the beginning of the application period next year if I have already completed modules worth 140 ECTS, but some of them are only rated as 'passed' or 'not passed'?
2b115b4d-0e2c-457a-8ac9-6ddcd2cb0d8f.answer: No, that's not a problem. For us, it is only important that you have completed at least 140 ECTS. If some modules are only rated as passed/not passed, that's not a problem. For the calculation of the average grade, we only consider the actually graded modules, and weight accordingly.

4ca3cbeb-b746-4c3a-88e7-0670a655b0b3.question: Would being exmatriculated due to academic misconduct from a previous masters degree at a german university affect the application to the AI in Society program at TUM?

4ff0f675-5ce5-497b-beee-1ee06a923e86.question: What degree students are eligible to apply for this course?
4ff0f675-5ce5-497b-beee-1ee06a923e86.answer: There is no restriction regarding Bachelor’s degree programs – we welcome students from all backgrounds. It is only important that you fulfil the requirements which are listed on our website.

3e61ef10-734c-44b2-8b8c-c808bf85e3fc.question: What kind of exams would fit the practical project requirement for the Master's degree 'AI in society'?

d9771256-7538-408d-9916-e95068cd042e.question: How is the course '[REDACTED]: Hands-on with bootstrap and [REDACTED]' at LMU evaluated?
d9771256-7538-408d-9916-e95068cd042e.answer: The final grade is entirely based on an oral exam. Students will be evaluated based on applying basic mathematical tools, analyzing a real-world problem using the tools covered in class, and interpreting the empirical results and having a rigorous discussion about it.

ae521808-4105-4244-a5a8-3da6d5cb701c.question: Can work experience be submitted as proof for the practical project requirement for the Master’s program “AI in Society” at TUM?
ae521808-4105-4244-a5a8-3da6d5cb701c.answer: If you choose to submit possible work experience as proof for practical project, we will need to see a work certificate from your employer.

bca3f539-a250-4b0b-9872-0ad8629a6be3.question: Can I apply for credit recognition for AI in Society courses with courses I have completed previously?
bca3f539-a250-4b0b-9872-0ad8629a6be3.answer: Yes, you can apply for credit recognition for AI in Society courses with courses you have completed previously. However, if the courses were counted for your application to the Master's program, they cannot be recognized again for the Master's program.

eea9ebaa-27cd-4d62-8952-82a23a26451e.question: Can anyone vote in the student representative election for the AI in Society program?
eea9ebaa-27cd-4d62-8952-82a23a26451e.answer: The voting link allows anyone to vote without restrictions, but the organizers are counting on the integrity of the students to prevent cheating.

31ce8ed5-2cba-4b54-ab37-316aa180ea08.question: When will the results of the student representative election for the Master’s program 'AI in Society' be available?
31ce8ed5-2cba-4b54-ab37-316aa180ea08.answer: The results of the student representative election will be available after the voting is completed by Wednesday at 6 PM.

17f12703-3122-4559-bd0b-4a9b5ff70002.question: What are the details of the proposed AI in Society master student gathering?
17f12703-3122-4559-bd0b-4a9b5ff70002.answer: The gathering is planned to be a Thanksgiving potluck. It is scheduled for the 28th from 5–9 p.m. The attendees will be AIS master's degree students and their acquaintances, as well as AIS faculties. The preferred location is one of the HfP areas, specifically the 1st floor big room. The organizers will comply with existing rules, including noise control and alcohol consumption, and will be responsible for cleaning up and waste management.

f77bfcbd-1c74-437f-8a39-f30f87f798fc.question: I am doing several extras courses that are not in our list of electives, what should I do to count those as electives?
f77bfcbd-1c74-437f-8a39-f30f87f798fc.answer: You can send the courses you are taking to the program heads. However, AIS students are intended to choose from the electives that are listed. You are free to take up additional courses, but they can’t be counted if they’re not part of the study degree.

908e8bbc-ad16-4464-bd66-c5a78b5bb531.question: How can I satisfy the requirement of a project worth at least 18 credit points for the Masters program of AI in Society at TU Munich, if I don't have a single project worth that much?
908e8bbc-ad16-4464-bd66-c5a78b5bb531.answer: You don’t need to provide one single project worth 18 credits, you can also specify multiple ones which in sum make up 18 credits. However, regarding your thesis: keep in mind that we can only count your thesis as a project module if it will be completed at the point of your application (i.e. the 15 ECTS are officially part of your transcript at that point).

16694bf2-8153-4af8-a226-c0cf92739700.question: Is there a limit to the number of project weeks a student can participate in?
16694bf2-8153-4af8-a226-c0cf92739700.answer: There is no limit of project weeks you can participate in, so if you really want to do multiple, you can. Keep in mind, however, that places are limited, and the participation in a project week needs you to dedicate (at least) a full week of your time during the semester.

447d6c3d-dc56-455d-af5d-c5c7e9bcb876.question: Can I ask for your help in the process of organizing this event?
447d6c3d-dc56-455d-af5d-c5c7e9bcb876.answer: If you need any of my help in the process, please let me know (also for announcing this get-together via email for everybody).

7eff0555-6a17-46a8-a92b-acb8017f4ecc.question: Can a BA thesis be used as ‘proof’ of a practical project for the 'AI in Society' program?
7eff0555-6a17-46a8-a92b-acb8017f4ecc.answer: The project described might be a bit insufficient, regarding the technical aspect. It is up to the selection committee to decide in the end, but it is encouraged to apply and describe your projects as best as possible. It is also suggested to submit all of the practical experience you have – you don’t have to choose only one of them.

ff1595ee-f4e9-459f-aff5-d5430ed208e0.question: Has the student sent the curriculum for the Sociology class?
ff1595ee-f4e9-459f-aff5-d5430ed208e0.answer: Yes, the student has sent the curriculum for the Sociology class.

a04c9acf-2a5b-4844-a822-056537caf42c.question: Is a meeting at 15:00 the next day acceptable to discuss the 'AI in Society' Master program?
a04c9acf-2a5b-4844-a822-056537caf42c.answer: Yes, a meeting at 15:00 the next day is acceptable.

1e0984cc-b0ab-4c9a-9117-1e2152aa63b7.question: Are there any specific formats or additional documentation requirements that may support my application?

9386eb44-8035-413d-a184-907d2d0b08b5.question: Is there a software known for conducting tests (MC and [REDACTED])?
9386eb44-8035-413d-a184-907d2d0b08b5.answer: For such tests, moodle is usually used.

f75a4578-f0e6-4a8e-9678-0d0e05254670.question: Can I discuss the admission requirements and course recognition for the 'AI in Society' Master program in person?
f75a4578-f0e6-4a8e-9678-0d0e05254670.answer: Yes, you can discuss your questions in person. Available appointment slots include tomorrow between 14-17, Wednesday between 11-12 or 14-17, or next Tuesday from 14-17. The meeting location is Richard-Wagner-Str. 1 (rightmost entrance), 3rd floor, room B.359. It would be best if you could bring along any documents you have, like transcripts of your studies.

7689cc74-eaa0-48df-98c0-ba03a6a4744e.question: How can a test be created on Moodle?
7689cc74-eaa0-48df-98c0-ba03a6a4744e.answer: To create a test on Moodle, first go to the course and click on 'Edit' at the top right. Then in the respective week where you want to insert the test, click on 'Create activity or material'. From there, you can select 'Test' and customize it as desired.

ec3cf6bb-4c9f-449f-a4dd-cb8dc5fe4306.question: When do applications open for the next winter semester for the MSc. AI in Society?
ec3cf6bb-4c9f-449f-a4dd-cb8dc5fe4306.answer: The applications for the next winter semester (starting in October 2025) will open in January/February 2025.

cc3c5783-e412-4b0a-b733-75db18ac2a30.question: Can I keep the grade of the recognized achievement in case I get a worse grade in the TUM course?

c4287989-35a7-4bdb-b3dd-894dc6fe7c7c.question: Is there a limit to the number of project weeks a student can participate in?
c4287989-35a7-4bdb-b3dd-894dc6fe7c7c.answer: No, there is no limit to the number of project weeks a student can participate in, but places are limited and participation requires dedicating at least a full week of your time during the semester.

e1ad8fa5-9ac6-4e91-8f99-8d9cc848b1e3.question: If the AI in [REDACTED]'s Program at TUM is not a fit for my qualifications, could you suggest any other programs at the university that may be more aligned with my goals?

57f37384-7c49-408b-89ea-2cce7b7f1827.question: Are there any specific formats or additional documentation requirements that may support my application to the Master’s program?

f3a0d6e0-21c6-4184-ba6a-d237e2937d0f.question: Can I discuss the 'AI in Society' Master program and its admission requirements in person?
f3a0d6e0-21c6-4184-ba6a-d237e2937d0f.answer: Yes, there is an option to discuss the program and its requirements in person or via a zoom meeting.

1a3257e0-2557-4cb3-b18a-f786765f6c00.question: Will everyone receive their admission result at the same time, and will the aptitude test be held on different dates?

be5c170d-7258-41b2-9e4e-2c06893da0d3.question: How many hours per week did I study for these subjects?
be5c170d-7258-41b2-9e4e-2c06893da0d3.answer: You estimated approximately 8 hours per week, but you are waiting for confirmation from your university.

51a0e113-e871-4d77-870c-4698cb88552c.question: How were the hours studied per week calculated for the application for recognition of credits?
51a0e113-e871-4d77-870c-4698cb88552c.answer: The hours studied per week were calculated by the applicant as approximately 8 hours, but they are clarifying it with the university where they took the course and waiting for their confirmation.

01e9e70d-41e0-4a3e-8856-a98229989b34.question: How are the hours studied per week calculated for the subjects?
01e9e70d-41e0-4a3e-8856-a98229989b34.answer: The hours studied per week for the subjects are calculated by the applicant, but should be confirmed by the university where the course was taken.

9de77ed5-cf69-4b71-ac8e-d9260a973db5.question: Can the student be manually added to the course after the registration has expired?

6a03fd61-d422-4981-9b91-c73024c28230.question: What is the solution if the registration period has ended and a student still needs to register?
6a03fd61-d422-4981-9b91-c73024c28230.answer: The course administrator can extend the registration period.

669174e6-de7b-41b2-940f-3cc0b6724974.question: What should a student do if they have enrolled successfully but the system shows registration expired?
669174e6-de7b-41b2-940f-3cc0b6724974.answer: The student might need help to be manually added into the course.

ab8de5aa-267a-45de-81cc-d532febdc959.question: How can I apply for recognition of credits for the AI in Society program at TUM?
ab8de5aa-267a-45de-81cc-d532febdc959.answer: To apply for recognition of credits, you need to fill the form provided on the TUM website and collect the documents listed on the TUM website. Then, send them to the provided email address. If you have modules you need to recognize as soon as possible, please send your documents by October 25th.

fb9aac42-00e9-4185-873c-0af758061d94.question: How can students register for the AI-based chatbot development course?
fb9aac42-00e9-4185-873c-0af758061d94.answer: Students can register for the course at https://campus.tum.de/tumonline/ee/ui/ca2/app/desktop/#/slc.tm.cp/student/courses/[NUMBER_REDACTED_AUTOMATICALLY]

8a64586d-19fa-40ca-b4b9-3129e0a11c63.question: How do I apply for recognition of credits?
8a64586d-19fa-40ca-b4b9-3129e0a11c63.answer: You need to fill the form provided on the AI in Society website and collect the documents listed on the TUM website. Send them to the provided email address. If you have modules you need to recognize as soon as possible, please send your documents by October 25th.

15652471-33c6-4ac9-9a9c-9a9763fbed1e.question: Will the admission still be valid if a student decides to reject the study place for deferring admission?
15652471-33c6-4ac9-9a9c-9a9763fbed1e.answer: Yes, the admission will still be valid for an indefinite time, so if the student decides to take the study place up again in one or two years, the university will still admit them.

c914635c-89d1-4d78-b1ab-9b3af2dece17.question: Who can I contact if I have any questions about the project week?
c914635c-89d1-4d78-b1ab-9b3af2dece17.answer: For any questions, please reach out to [REDACTED], who is responsible for this project week.

e10f7c51-47dc-4cee-94ee-b0eba85ec617.question: How should the teaching obligation for the semester in which I started at TUM be calculated?
e10f7c51-47dc-4cee-94ee-b0eba85ec617.answer: The teaching obligation for this semester should be calculated proportionally to the lecture days that were still left in this summer semester. Regularly you have a 2.5 SWS teaching obligation per semester, but for the summer semester 2023 it should be less.

d604d359-89de-4638-a5b6-5983a674344c.question: Can I know beforehand whether a course will be recognized by the AI in Society program or not?
d604d359-89de-4638-a5b6-5983a674344c.answer: You can write to the professor of the module in AI in Society and ask, but they won’t give you a 100% sure answer, because these cases need to be checked properly and formally.

811f352c-823c-455e-823a-3da9231845d2.question: Who should be contacted for any questions about the project week?
811f352c-823c-455e-823a-3da9231845d2.answer: For any questions, students should reach out to the person responsible for the project week.

e9e7ebda-4fac-4da3-b2d1-651a369be75d.question: You still didn't answer my original question regarding the two different dates of tuition/semester fees which I found on your website. Can you help me to verify it?

e340217d-4315-41b3-b105-71de45c02365.question: What are the steps to complete enrollment at TUM?
e340217d-4315-41b3-b105-71de45c02365.answer: To complete enrollment, the student must officially accept the offer of admission in TUMonline, transfer the semester fee by the deadline, and submit any missing documents, including the signed enrollment application, to the Admissions and Enrollment Office within the designated timeframe. Some documents can be directly uploaded in TUMonline, while others must be sent in hardcopy by mail.

9b36b477-5259-492e-91e0-15131c0a5177.question: What are the steps to enroll at TUM?
9b36b477-5259-492e-91e0-15131c0a5177.answer: To enroll at TUM, please send in a signed application for enrollment form, together with the other required hardcopy documents listed in your TUMonline account. Please enroll as soon as possible, preferably until the first day of the semester. You will receive your student status and will be able to register for classes and exams only after enrollment. Before you are enrolled, it is not possible to participate in any classes or coursework, and you will not receive your TUM student card. All steps towards enrollment (postal delivery and processing) take time. Please act in a timely manner, so that you can be enrolled at the beginning of the semester.

069cd4df-38fa-4db1-9ad9-d5c7f3ee7293.question: Can I get a letter confirming the exemption from the German language requirement for my program?

48c1a7c5-511e-4003-ae9d-baf874f931f6.question: Can you provide an extension letter or supporting document for the visa application?

63baf6ca-61b3-4e48-b9ce-6c7c38f68ca3.question: Specifically, I am also concerned about the semester in which I started at TUM: The contract start was 1.7.2023. That means the teaching assignment for this semester should be calculated proportionally to the lecture days that were still left in this summer semester. I usually have a 2.5 SWS teaching obligation per semester, but for the summer semester 2023 it should be less.
63baf6ca-61b3-4e48-b9ce-6c7c38f68ca3.answer: As far as I know there was a reduction from the dean due to the study coordination tasks. The central department confirmed 0 until 01.2.2025, then it is 2.5 SWS.

f68cb395-100e-4cbf-b8c7-51cc519dddb1.question: What information is needed when sending emails about specific students to the Office for Application and Matriculation?
f68cb395-100e-4cbf-b8c7-51cc519dddb1.answer: When sending such emails, it is requested to include the student's matriculation number to facilitate the search process.

f2779c15-c4c3-4a61-bd44-1a1235e2d7fc.question: Where can a student find information about their degree and the corresponding documents?
f2779c15-c4c3-4a61-bd44-1a1235e2d7fc.answer: Information about a student's degree and the corresponding documents can be found on the website of the TU Munich.

67a5e654-b8a4-456b-bbdd-8164447a71c1.question: Is there any way I could still register for the other courses as '[REDACTED]' and gain access to the Moodle content while my enrollment is pending?
67a5e654-b8a4-456b-bbdd-8164447a71c1.answer: You should have received an email from TUM/your study coordinator, congratulating you about finishing your Bachelor’s degree. Please forward me this email. I will them forward it to the matriculation office. For them, this will be counted as proof of you having completed your studies, so you do not have to wait for your official certificates. After this, you should be matriculated pretty quickly, allowing you to register for our courses as an AI in Society student.

9a3cfea3-2770-425f-9b79-a4e22d8c4ce6.question: When will the lecture schedules be available?
9a3cfea3-2770-425f-9b79-a4e22d8c4ce6.answer: The lecture schedules are not yet finalized and will be published on the website in due course before the start of the semester.

a3255309-94f0-45af-b46c-7de262841b98.question: At TUM Online, do we have classes on the 16.10 for Foundations of AI and [REDACTED]?
a3255309-94f0-45af-b46c-7de262841b98.answer: No, the first tutorial for Foundations of AI & [REDACTED] won't take place on 16.10 since there will be nothing to discuss yet. The first lecture is on 18.10 and the first regular tutorial will be on 23.10.

948653a0-8d3c-4725-aff6-17f68183f15c.answer: You should reach out to the program head for information about partnerships.

4f3de94e-5510-4dd7-a175-bc6bd9880691.question: Can the invitation link for the new AIS Whatsapp group be shared?
4f3de94e-5510-4dd7-a175-bc6bd9880691.answer: Yes, the invitation link for the new AIS Whatsapp group can be shared via slides at the welcome event and via email with all students.

678e0792-3bca-4dc5-9378-720ec7883a93.question: Does it matter during which period of the application opening (between February and May 31st) I apply for the program?
678e0792-3bca-4dc5-9378-720ec7883a93.answer: It technically does not matter when in this period you send your application. However, due to the big amount applications, this year we had to split up the aptitude test into multiple dates. Please don’t take “first come, first serve” as a solid rule here, but I would recommend submitting your application rather sooner than later.

c42270d8-e4cd-4e8c-9083-6e66161616f7.question: Should I choose my preference according to my previous programming knowledge?
c42270d8-e4cd-4e8c-9083-6e66161616f7.answer: No, it has nothing to do with your previous programming knowledge.

f8755f39-784d-4018-b0c8-a369ac9adefd.question: What to do if you are not able to attend the course 'Introduction to Programming & [REDACTED]' because it was scheduled before the official beginning of the semester?
f8755f39-784d-4018-b0c8-a369ac9adefd.answer: The course has been shifted to take place during the semester, on Tuesdays from 09:00 - 16:00, from October 15 to November 12. You will be able to attend this course in person, as well as online.

fc468dac-5339-48e2-9462-7daa8ec520a9.answer: If you want to defer your admission to next year, you can do so. In this case, you now need to decline the offer online. Then, next year you apply again with all documents, however, you will be automatically admitted by the matriculation office since you already had received an offer. So, you won’t go through the selection process again next year.

85939ee7-a5fb-43e1-8bbe-dc52f8dae477.answer: If you want to defer your admission to next year, you can do so. In this case, you now need to decline the offer online. 84e45374-51a7-41db-9409-967c5b9c1c39.answer: The next scheduled event is on the 19th of September.

54fca388-f21a-4199-99d4-44b2ff9e52b8.question: What should I do if I am unable to start studying from 1st October due to visa delays?
54fca388-f21a-4199-99d4-44b2ff9e52b8.answer: The lectures are offered in a hybrid format, i.e. they are streamed online in parallel. You will be able to follow them from your home country. Therefore, if you arrive 1-2 months later, it will not be a problem.

62cac089-9076-40a6-a4b7-a6dce9d54e11.question: What are the available timeslots for the interview for the M.Sc. AI in Society at TUM?
62cac089-9076-40a6-a4b7-a6dce9d54e11.answer: The available timeslots are from 09:30 – 11:00 and 13:00 – 17:00 CEST (Germany time). The interview spans a time of 30 minutes.

7fc267bf-89a1-4ed9-bc7d-7d87795cf231.question: What is the earliest timeslot available for the aptitude interview on the day?
7fc267bf-89a1-4ed9-bc7d-7d87795cf231.answer: The earliest timeslot available on the day is 14:30 – 15:00.

f1ad4ff7-510d-4013-b99a-2880196c5503.question: Do you offer a working student program in parallel to the AI in Society program at TUM, or any of your engineering master’s programs?
f1ad4ff7-510d-4013-b99a-2880196c5503.answer: TUM doesn’t specifically offer working student programs. Normally what people do in Germany, is to apply for working student jobs on their own, independently from the study program.

5ae6ddc6-0a29-4ffa-b8f8-9cebb92d7fa8.question: Does my current status as a student in an EU country affect the tuition fee requirements for my application to the AI in Society program at the Technical University of Munich?

c58c2b31-466a-42d3-ab4b-ffd3c265d42c.question: Is it possible to submit independent or other project work that I have completed for other parties for admission to the AI in Society - MSc course?
c58c2b31-466a-42d3-ab4b-ffd3c265d42c.answer: The practical project does not exclusively need to be from your bachelor’s studies. Work experience or internships are also counted. It is important that there is some sort of proof of your project, i.e. that it can be seen that you did not just invent it. For example, a statement from your employer, or a certificate of participation in any external projects.

81e8f84f-ce95-43ca-be07-e2e50487aefe.question: What if the fields provided aren't enough to list up to 140 credits as most of the courses on my transcript are 2 and 3 credits each?

d1fa31db-4bbf-41d5-b913-b297e9d48da1.answer: Yes, an introductory event for all incoming AI in Society students is being planned. The professors will introduce themselves and information around the program will be provided. This will be in October, at some point before the start of the semester.

e0c3630b-8dfb-47fb-9dde-04d87a2c8977.answer: The available timeslots are from 09:30 – 11:00 and 13:00 – 17:00 CEST (Germany time). The interview spans a time of 30 minutes.

4c72f129-b48d-4447-8d8f-1f1e4c3be587.answer: Not all lecture plans have been completed yet, which is why you can't find them on TUMonline. A timetable for the first semester will be posted on the website soon.

5a21aedb-7fe0-44b6-ab14-2277102cfad9.answer: Please let me know your preferred timeslot (30 minutes within the above times) by September 12th, 23:59.

40c25b1d-52cf-4f0a-873d-f2da78ecdcb4.question: When will the final decision be made after the aptitude interview for the M.Sc. AI in Society at TUM?
40c25b1d-52cf-4f0a-873d-f2da78ecdcb4.answer: The final decision will be made right at the end of the interview. If an admission is decided, it can be issued on the same day.

759cc7c2-ecb5-4dbf-a48c-5ce9a0f2b6c9.answer: The final decision will be made right at the end of the interview. If the decision is for admission, it can be issued on the same day.

d6666d0d-5f47-4abe-886c-932fc0fea54d.answer: You should let us know your preferred timeslot by September 12th, 23:59.

ffc19aab-9fff-4ccf-9cb4-eb580bfc631c.answer: Given your high motivation and great performance in the written test, the program heads have decided to let you proceed to the interview phase.

2311d980-c52d-4f05-a17e-c8918a8c2184.answer: Unfortunately, your candidacy has led to a rejection. The points you scored in the test and from your degree grades do not pass our thresholds.

5afddf61-9ffe-4603-8306-761a920fe08b.answer: In the coming days, you will receive the link to the moodle test. There, you should 1) choose your preferred exam modality (on-/off-campus) and 2) take the demo test to make yourself familiar with the test environment. If you choose the off-campus version, you will also be guided through the Proctorio installation and payment process.

10c9d1d3-6643-4d9c-ab4c-ce427fe6898a.answer: The dates and times for the lectures are currently being finalized and are subject to change. Once finalized, the information can be found on the website.

7fee376f-b551-4875-a3d8-ba6aac55a9bb.answer: Some documents in your application are still not marked as “OK”. The matriculation office needs to be consulted about this. 12156949-c606-47c1-af67-0d36bb7df3e5.question: How relevant is proficiency in German for succeeding in the Master’s program and securing job opportunities related to the field? Also, does TUM offer German language courses as an extracurricular option included in the Master's program fees?
12156949-c606-47c1-af67-0d36bb7df3e5.answer: German language is not required for our Master’s program, as all modules are taught in English. 36e41b65-0724-48bb-879e-de2d7628026e.question: I am considering transferring to the AI Master's program at [REDACTED] University of Munich (LMU) after completing my first year at Utrecht University. b439568a-674e-4b4c-8b88-064416b42c29.answer: No, the decision made by the committee is final and cannot be reconsidered.

d199bb9a-28ae-4396-95a5-8ea9543d16a7.answer: Since you are transferring to the LMU, and not TUM, you should contact them instead.

220edd55-1f6c-4c39-9137-5547c677f64d.answer: If you will be in Munich physically a bit later, it should be no problem since we will be offering the first semester lectures online. This way, you will not miss any content.

3d2104fe-a940-42b1-be40-f3fc4caaba95.question: Will all the lectures for the AI in Society course take place at the Garching campus?
3d2104fe-a940-42b1-be40-f3fc4caaba95.answer: No, most of the lectures will take place in the city center. Only one module each in the second and third semesters usually takes place in Garching.

ec52c47b-9688-4637-8cec-32aa9e5029c0.question: Can the committee reconsider a rejected application if the applicant has now received a scholarship?

3af35811-2331-4e85-b7e1-438a2d96fc38.answer: For information about tuition fees, refer to the TUM student information: https://www.tum.de/en/studies/support-and-advice/support-during-studies/student-information

d6cf6baf-1a3e-4117-8d0e-8171bae9cb44.question: Are there any introductory and orientation events for new AI in Society students before the courses start?
d6cf6baf-1a3e-4117-8d0e-8171bae9cb44.answer: Yes, a welcome event for all new AI in Society students is planned at the beginning of October, before the lectures start.

5906616f-0e84-4808-a365-6d91943cc0dc.answer: For the time being (while you are not yet in Munich), you can participate in the courses online. We will make sure they will all be streamed in parallel for people who could not make it here physically in time.

38539fbb-0c6e-43cd-8afe-3c4754b61d10.answer: Yes, you can apply for DAAD scholarships, assuming their deadline has not passed yet.

c4e8d5e4-888f-47fa-b156-5eb943388fec.question: What is the correct email address for submitting the enrollment documents at TUM?

f70244d3-2d12-4a57-a37a-96b44425fbaf.answer: The aptitude test is scheduled for September 3rd.

658bc18c-1d7d-490c-980e-de3aa79e5cf2.answer: The department you actually received your degree from should issue the letter verifying your English language proficiency.

5bc01c75-3a2b-4fae-81b0-c49a4d6b112d.answer: The letter verifying English language proficiency is required for a visa application in India, as the IELTS score is 1 year old, even though the validity for IELTS is 2 years.

dfe241fa-fba5-44ca-920b-3bd223c09c51.answer: Please upload the correct document if you have it.

4cf58a6b-116f-4700-8b71-c6f97aba8a93.question: Is the AI in Society program at TUM also taught in the summer semester 2025, or is the start always only possible in the winter semester?
4cf58a6b-116f-4700-8b71-c6f97aba8a93.answer: Enrollment for AI in Society is generally only possible in the winter semester. The next possible start of studies would be in October 2025.

491d2e5a-ccb8-411a-a8da-0c930be34695.question: When are the classes scheduled to start, and is there a specific timetable available that I can review?
491d2e5a-ccb8-411a-a8da-0c930be34695.answer: Classes at TUM will officially start on October 14th. Regarding a specific timetable for the first semester, please check back soon on our website.

699b1888-df01-4edd-b281-23d7705af416.question: Can the university provide a letter verifying English language proficiency for visa application purposes?

931256fe-4fd7-4e4e-8071-8dff60f081d9.question: Can the university provide a letter verifying my English language proficiency for my visa application?
931256fe-4fd7-4e4e-8071-8dff60f081d9.answer: The department you received your degree from should issue you a verification of English language proficiency. The university cannot provide this verification if you have not studied with them.

c50db80c-63d3-4948-85ef-ec3bf4422dc1.question: Can I request a new interview after my application has been rejected?
c50db80c-63d3-4948-85ef-ec3bf4422dc1.answer: No, a new interview cannot be offered once the decision has already been made.

c353a701-d6c3-4633-a453-356071095b2f.question: What are the requirements for taking the aptitude test online for the Master’s program in AI in Society at TUM?

ce1ef89c-4804-471b-a3a1-0059b5674aa4.question: I have been living in Germany for more than 5 years and according to TUM terms & conditions, I should not pay the €4000 tuition fee for foreign countries. However, my fee status indicates that I have to pay this amount. How should I proceed?
ce1ef89c-4804-471b-a3a1-0059b5674aa4.answer: For issues regarding study fees, please reach out to the office for fees and scholarships at the provided email address.

53ff324c-657d-47f6-bc73-07c294c0179a.question: Can I participate in the courses online if I am not able to be in Munich physically in time?
53ff324c-657d-47f6-bc73-07c294c0179a.answer: Yes, for the time being (while you are not yet in Munich), you can participate in the courses online. They will all be streamed in parallel for people who could not make it here physically in time.

0690428b-c427-4f62-b16c-218b6e4ea601.question: Where can Ukrainian students who have fled Ukraine due to the war apply for a waiver for the master's degree program 'AI in Society'?
0690428b-c427-4f62-b16c-218b6e4ea601.answer: For this, please reach out to the contact given at the bottom of this page: https://www.tum.de/en/studies/fees-and-financial-aid/scholarships/tum-scholarships/scholarship/urgent-fonds-students-ukraine-war

b33e02bc-dab3-4aa1-b5f6-9c4013650b0f.question: Are there any specific networking options, groups, or events organised for students of the AI in Society program at TUM?
b33e02bc-dab3-4aa1-b5f6-9c4013650b0f.answer: There is currently no specific networking events for the AI in Society program. However, students will have plenty of opportunities to connect with their classmates as they will have the same study plan and attend the same courses.

e5a8531b-ff1b-4814-b67a-b335e9e716a7.answer: A consultation is currently not possible as the respondent will not be available throughout August. It is suggested to send specific questions and concerns via email.

0746cf6a-5723-45aa-99bf-715d64f9c7e8.answer: The university will automatically register the program for Bafög at some point, but it seems this has not happened yet.

ca35ba68-2829-4f00-a3d4-1df55581cdad.answer: Yes, you can reject the offer now and instead accept the study place next year. We will still have it in the system that you had passed all requirements and will be admitted.

9095889c-724c-4a8d-a253-2ed09fe12fb7.question: Can I submit digital versions of my transcripts and degrees for enrollment at TUM?

16ae4138-4976-46ea-9516-6312279b1559.question: Could you let me know my final score for Level 1 of this process?
16ae4138-4976-46ea-9516-6312279b1559.answer: You received 12 points for your previous grades, and 31 points in the test. In total, you landed at 43 points.

708e4e6a-afb1-4bc9-8f83-5e657c315d98.question: What should I do if I need to change my selected timeslot for the aptitude interview for the M.Sc. AI in Society at TUM?
708e4e6a-afb1-4bc9-8f83-5e657c315d98.answer: If you want to change your selection later, you will be able to do so yourself. However, you should let the team know in case you had to change your slot, especially if it's last minute.

6851920e-5143-490a-9f00-fe03cba7b7fd.question: When will I receive the Zoom link for my aptitude interview for the M.Sc. AI in Society at TUM?
6851920e-5143-490a-9f00-fe03cba7b7fd.answer: You will receive your personal Zoom link at least 12 hours in advance to your interview.

85cb88d9-4754-4f15-8dba-0cd36e39b910.question: Can you tell me whether I can still apply for any scholarship program to finance my studies?
85cb88d9-4754-4f15-8dba-0cd36e39b910.answer: For questions regarding scholarships, please contact TUM’s scholarship office directly: https://www.tum.de/en/studies/fees-and-financial-aid/scholarships

4555ac51-cbfe-402c-ab7a-94c366d956b4.question: What happens if I encounter a technical error during the aptitude test for the MSc. AI in Society program?
4555ac51-cbfe-402c-ab7a-94c366d956b4.answer: In case of a technical error, you will be added to the moodle exam and sent a link to participate on another date. If anything goes wrong, there will be a third test date, to which you will be invited.

0328040b-d26e-43d1-b2ac-7a9ee3ce8a73.question: At which TUM location do the events for the M.Sc. AI in Society program take place, or do they take place at several locations?
0328040b-d26e-43d1-b2ac-7a9ee3ce8a73.answer: The events are somewhat distributed throughout the city center. They will mainly take place in the following buildings: Richard-Wagner-Str. 1, Marsstr. 20-22, Arcisstr. 21 (possibly).

59d01ed1-4e89-4b51-bcc2-673c73684c0f.question: Do you have any relevant data on actual graduate outcomes of the MSc AI in Society program, such as hiring firms, average/median starting salary, and countries graduates are hired in?
59d01ed1-4e89-4b51-bcc2-673c73684c0f.answer: Since the coming semester is the very first semester we are offering this program, we do not have data on graduate outcomes yet.

c4a322aa-3307-426d-9da9-d234bc436a14.question: Where are the AI in Society lectures taking place?
c4a322aa-3307-426d-9da9-d234bc436a14.answer: The lectures are planned to be organized in the city center, either at Richard-Wagner-Str. 1, Marsstr. 20-22, or Arcisstr. 21. Some courses from other departments might be offered in Garching, but the majority will take place in the city center.

5b0c68bd-0d1a-4643-bb7c-0eafc3d9f4b5.question: What is the format of the aptitude test?
5b0c68bd-0d1a-4643-bb7c-0eafc3d9f4b5.answer: The test will consist of 35 multiple choice questions spanned over 90 minutes, and will be held over TUM's internal moodle platform. You will be allowed to use a calculator, as well as a piece of paper and pen to help you.

eeae8458-6850-4c60-b6bb-2c3343f7788d.question: What will happen since I missed the aptitude test for the AI in Society program?
eeae8458-6850-4c60-b6bb-2c3343f7788d.answer: You will be invited to the third test date that is currently being planned.

a18dc2b4-042e-4afc-8a74-db04cc1a5dfd.question: Why haven't I received a link to the AI in Society program aptitude test?
a18dc2b4-042e-4afc-8a74-db04cc1a5dfd.answer: Your application has been marked as insufficient regarding one of your documents, which is why you have not been invited. Please check the comment regarding your application.

15bed8f9-8229-4d7b-8f2b-9a14d85d0be8.question: What should I do after receiving the link to the moodle test?
15bed8f9-8229-4d7b-8f2b-9a14d85d0be8.answer: After receiving the link to the moodle test, you should 1) choose your preferred exam modality (on-/off-campus) and 2) take the demo test to make yourself familiar with the test environment. If you choose the off-campus version, you will also be guided through the Proctorio installation and payment there.

e286c1f1-6c32-47d9-8742-d1d0580d6340.question: If there are some technical issues during the test tomorrow, is there a contact person or an email which I can use for help?
e286c1f1-6c32-47d9-8742-d1d0580d6340.answer: If there are any technical problems, there is a zoom call hotline as well as a phone number given on the moodle exam page.

e78570fd-7def-481d-92f9-34047c66c098.question: What should I do if I can't make any foreign currency transactions with my card to pay for the off-campus variant of the aptitude test?

cd35f67f-79c8-4f3e-a962-454916105e26.question: When is the third aptitude test planned?
cd35f67f-79c8-4f3e-a962-454916105e26.answer: The third test is planned for September currently.

5d6551f1-9386-44a1-888f-074ba6aa36a1.question: What happens if I have not received any additional information pertaining to the aptitude test the day before the scheduled test?
5d6551f1-9386-44a1-888f-074ba6aa36a1.answer: There seems to have been a technical mistake. The team will try to add you to the moodle exam today and send you the link to participate tomorrow. Should anything go wrong, there will be a third test date, to which you will be invited.

55d2b12b-7363-4bc3-9ef4-6dd3877f1e92.question: Why haven't I received the link for the Aptitude test and the payment link for the TUM AI program?
55d2b12b-7363-4bc3-9ef4-6dd3877f1e92.answer: There seems to have been a technical mistake. The team will try to add you to the moodle exam and send you the link to participate. If anything goes wrong, there will be a third test date to which you will be invited.

5cba680a-ed07-4c66-9900-83ed35151897.question: Are we allowed to have something written before hand on our piece of paper for the exam?
5cba680a-ed07-4c66-9900-83ed35151897.answer: No, you are not allowed to have information written already. You are only allowed a calculator and a blank piece of paper.

efba00de-7285-48d6-901b-53a350a310c2.question: I uploaded my VPD before the deadline (July 15th), why is it not marked as 'OK'?
efba00de-7285-48d6-901b-53a350a310c2.answer: The matriculation office needs to assess the VPD, and it has not been marked as 'OK' yet. The process will be discussed with the matriculation office and you will be informed about what you need to do.

57d78a16-6d39-4c95-8de5-99fb9214d7d7.question: What should I do if I received the invitation to the test but have not received a link to partake in the aptitude test?

d23a834e-bc08-40e2-8118-38d540cdfa7e.question: What is the location for the on-campus variant of the aptitude test?
d23a834e-bc08-40e2-8118-38d540cdfa7e.answer: The on-campus variant of the aptitude test will take place in Marsstr. 20-22, 80335 Munich, room 605, 6th floor.

b458d302-1ece-4988-90d4-3bb908c5d175.question: What are the options for taking the aptitude test for the AI in Society program at TUM?
b458d302-1ece-4988-90d4-3bb908c5d175.answer: The test for the winter semester 2024/25 will be primarily held online. Should you want to take the test in person (TUM, Munich city center) instead, this possibility will also be provided. If you choose to write the test online, you will be monitored via an automated proctoring software, which will demand a fee of 25$. If you do not agree to partake in the online test with the automated monitoring procedure, the only other option is to take the test in person.

6c70f57a-20c7-4098-92c6-5b4097893068.question: When can I expect to receive the formal offer for the AI in Society master's program?
6c70f57a-20c7-4098-92c6-5b4097893068.answer: The formal offer has been issued now.

9b538852-4d95-4dbe-a4a6-f6f450275acf.question: What is the format and duration of the aptitude test for the AI in Society program at TUM?
9b538852-4d95-4dbe-a4a6-f6f450275acf.answer: The test will be conducted in English language and span 90 minutes. You will be asked to answer multiple-choice questions.

6fe5e149-b726-4282-8a14-e53b398a88cb.question: Can I use a calculator during the aptitude test for the Master’s program in AI in Society?
6fe5e149-b726-4282-8a14-e53b398a88cb.answer: During the test, you are allowed to use a calculator.

fb1f1c8f-4a52-4c70-bf0a-a0efc79853ad.question: What are the requirements for the on-campus variant of the AI in Society aptitude test?
fb1f1c8f-4a52-4c70-bf0a-a0efc79853ad.answer: The on-campus variant will not require any fee, as you will be monitored by staff in person. You will need to bring your laptop to take the test. The test will not be written on paper. Should you not be able to bring a laptop for the test, please let us know in advance. We will provide you with a laptop in this case.

e43080a3-7e5f-4f5a-8a4a-d1b905866bb2.question: Due to a time difference mix-up, would it be possible for us to reschedule for a different time today?
e43080a3-7e5f-4f5a-8a4a-d1b905866bb2.answer: In that case, we will offer you a second interview date at the end of July. Please await further information regarding timeslots.

04b4b55c-8115-4dbe-b502-ced7102dd50d.question: What materials are allowed during the aptitude test for the Master’s program in AI in Society?
04b4b55c-8115-4dbe-b502-ced7102dd50d.answer: During the test, you are allowed to use a calculator.

d85f79c5-b981-474f-95d7-ad20dc95059c.question: When is the second test date for those who did not receive an invitation for the first one?
d85f79c5-b981-474f-95d7-ad20dc95059c.answer: The second test date is on July 16th, from 10:45 - 12:15 CEST. However, for applicants where we are still waiting on the VPD, there will be another test date in September.

fb070b7c-4327-49f5-96b5-6f6f0fdd3812.answer: For this question, I would kindly refer you to the center of fees and scholarships: https://www.tum.de/en/studies/fees

9a75de04-655b-4d4b-ab46-1318ee5fe1ad.question: What does 'Level 2' mean in terms of the total score for the entry process to the AI in Society program at TUM?
9a75de04-655b-4d4b-ab46-1318ee5fe1ad.answer: The score for level 2 refers to the score you receive in the interview. The interview, however, is an optional step and not everyone will need to go through one.

3f2dcfa2-1287-4c47-b28b-796035c9ce71.question: Should we give people the opportunity to move the test date (from the second to the third test date in September), or should we just say this is the only opportunity?
3f2dcfa2-1287-4c47-b28b-796035c9ce71.answer: No, we don't have to offer a third date. If we can do without it, that would be great, as we are already starting the programming course in the week before the start of the semester.

ad5ffca4-f3af-43ef-8a0e-b88457887ab5.answer: The test for the winter semester 2024/25 will be primarily held online. Should you want to take the test in person (TUM, Munich city center) instead, that option is also available. If you choose to write the test online, you will be monitored via an automated proctoring software, which will demand a fee of 25$. If you do not agree to partake in the online test with the automated monitoring procedure, the only other option is to take the test in person.

5c3749c8-b886-40d2-b388-4f7ce19c38f5.question: Can I take the online aptitude test for the Master’s program in AI in Society at TUM without being monitored?
5c3749c8-b886-40d2-b388-4f7ce19c38f5.answer: The monitoring form of the test is aligned according to TUM ProLehre standards and is a standard procedure. If you choose to take the test without being monitored, your test results may be disregarded.

1013c369-3b0b-4836-aea0-3db81ff790da.question: How can an applicant select a timeslot for the interview?
1013c369-3b0b-4836-aea0-3db81ff790da.answer: Applicants can select a timeslot for the interview using the provided link. They will need to enter their email address and full name, then choose one timeslot that works best for them. Each timeslot can only be selected by one person, therefore the distribution of slots works by the principle “first come, first serve”. After selecting, they need to submit their answer.

9bba91a5-8fc3-4587-a3b4-198117b24863.question: What resources are allowed during the aptitude test for the Master’s program in AI in Society?
9bba91a5-8fc3-4587-a3b4-198117b24863.answer: During the test, applicants are allowed to use a calculator.

9b4ed8eb-a28d-4b5e-98a6-fa3399ed87d7.question: What are the reasons for a project not being okay?
9b4ed8eb-a28d-4b5e-98a6-fa3399ed87d7.answer: A project may not be okay if it has less than the required ECTS, if the technical aspect is not given sufficiently, if the interdisciplinary aspect is not given sufficiently, or if it is unclear which module the project refers to, making it impossible to match ECTS.

d69e1a04-066e-4688-9dd9-bf30d32b7bf4.question: What is the procedure for applicants who have not yet received an invitation to the aptitude test for the M.Sc. AI in Society at TUM?
d69e1a04-066e-4688-9dd9-bf30d32b7bf4.answer: There will be a second test date on July 16th, from 10:45 - 12:15 CEST. Applicants who did not yet hear back from the university (and were not declined either), should await further feedback regarding their application in the coming weeks. The university will finish checking the remaining applicants and invite them to the second test, should all their documents suffice.

eefe5f9c-1251-4f1a-8a3e-df2300ea38ee.question: Does the kulibri website adjust the interview times to the user’s timezone?
eefe5f9c-1251-4f1a-8a3e-df2300ea38ee.answer: Yes, the website seems to adjust the times to the user’s timezone.

d3f84d5b-7ac1-458c-ac0f-d4d29f1f850c.question: What is the intake rate for 'AI in Society' for the academic year 2024/25, i.e. how many students have applied and are expected to be admitted to the master program for this upcoming semester?
d3f84d5b-7ac1-458c-ac0f-d4d29f1f850c.answer: The amount of students who will start their studies with us is relatively hard to tell at the moment, since the selection progress is still ongoing.

ad604d97-1b19-4be6-bca4-b790940b74c1.question: What is the procedure for applicants who have not yet received an invitation to the aptitude test for the AI in Society program at TUM?
ad604d97-1b19-4be6-bca4-b790940b74c1.answer: There will be a second test date. Should you be one of the applicants who did not yet hear back from us (and were not declined either), please await further feedback regarding your application in the coming weeks from us. We will finish checking the remaining applicants and invite you to the second test, should all your documents suffice.

a5e0da84-9094-4f99-8d80-a4387d23e402.answer: If you have not received an invitation to the aptitude test, there will be a second test date. You should await further feedback regarding your application in the coming weeks.

f9cd6a17-2ac1-45f2-8564-0d47cb40730a.question: What is the plan for applicants who have not yet received feedback for the AI in Society program at TUM?
f9cd6a17-2ac1-45f2-8564-0d47cb40730a.answer: The plan for applicants who have not yet received feedback is to finish checking the remaining applicants and invite them to a second test, should all their documents suffice.

5eb4117f-b410-4404-840e-362a92dd1544.question: Will I receive a confirmation email after selecting a timeslot for the aptitude interview for the M.Sc. AI in Society at TUM?
5eb4117f-b410-4404-840e-362a92dd1544.answer: No, as soon as you have selected a time slot, you can think of it as confirmed – there will be no additional email confirming your timeslot. You will receive your personal Zoom link at least 12 hours in advance to your interview.

7a50e412-1495-4ead-9562-d4e6193b2e2f.question: Would it be possible to get an answer for the acceptance to the Master AI in Society before the 15th of July?
7a50e412-1495-4ead-9562-d4e6193b2e2f.answer: No, it is not possible to provide an answer for the acceptance to the Master AI in Society before the 15th of July as the aptitude test is scheduled for July 16th.

167c69e8-dea7-409f-a4bb-8cf792387685.answer: The website automatically converts the times to your timezone. So, what you are seeing is just according to your timezone, not CEST.

46a61459-1ead-4a4e-baf4-08b364a21408.answer: The solution is to choose a different timeslot from the ones that are still available.

eecbc5e3-3366-414b-892a-174514e8c458.answer: As soon as you have selected a time slot, you can think of it as confirmed – there will be no additional email confirming your timeslot.

70925c81-543b-42f0-8d72-f63cd006704a.question: Will I receive a confirmation email after selecting a timeslot for the interview for the M.Sc. AI in Society at TUM?
70925c81-543b-42f0-8d72-f63cd006704a.answer: No, there will be no additional email confirming your timeslot. As soon as you have selected a time slot, you can think of it as confirmed. You will receive your personal Zoom link at least 12 hours in advance to your interview.

ff51557b-26d9-4ed3-87aa-6fa13cd81ca3.answer: No, there will be no additional email confirming your timeslot. As soon as you have selected a time slot, you can think of it as confirmed. You will receive your personal Zoom link at least 12 hours in advance to your interview.

04397a14-a397-4cec-8d14-2aff453f47e1.question: What should an applicant do if they want to change their selected timeslot for the interview for the M.Sc. AI in Society at TUM?

777aa33a-ada5-4ccc-8caa-f8c12d99df39.answer: Yes, some information regarding the contents of the test has been published.

a3b7c7c0-bb80-48fc-8a1c-010cf501bc19.question: What should be done if the processing period for the VPD is extended and affects the ability to meet the submission deadline?
a3b7c7c0-bb80-48fc-8a1c-010cf501bc19.answer: You should apply for the VPD with all necessary documents by May 31st and state this in your application to TUM. The deadline for submitting the final VPD is extended to whenever uni-assist sends you the final document.

d320d46c-4f50-42fb-9093-5a95e9baa589.answer: If the practical modules appear in [REDACTED], that's enough as proof. However, you will be asked in a form to describe the projects in more detail so that we can also imagine something in terms of content.

b6002825-4b6f-4ddb-a61b-843968548054.question: What are the tuition fees for the Master's program in AI in Society for EU students?
b6002825-4b6f-4ddb-a61b-843968548054.answer: Students from Germany and the EU study at TUM free of tuition. You can find this information here: https://www.tum.de/en/studies/fees/tuition

1092c727-ccf0-4e3f-a865-229a8210ab86.question: As an international student who already has a degree from Germany, will I be subject to the international tuition fee for the AI in Society course?
1092c727-ccf0-4e3f-a865-229a8210ab86.answer: For this, please contact TUM’s student information center: https://www.tum.de/en/studies/support-and-advice/support-during-studies/student-information

4a11ab9f-32c0-45e6-8a43-b6e9c2c104e2.question: Do the courses I have taken and the projects I have done meet the practical part of the requirements for the AI in Society program at TUM?

e4588d97-c980-4309-9c65-cb4ccabc345c.question: If I received a notification that the document was not Okay and now I have reuploaded a correction in TUM Online, do I need to actually start another application?
e4588d97-c980-4309-9c65-cb4ccabc345c.answer: You do not need to start a new application – if you uploaded new documents, this application will be checked again.

3f8c2905-b581-4376-bf86-740326a45924.question: Does writing [REDACTED] fulfill the requirement for a practical part of the application?
3f8c2905-b581-4376-bf86-740326a45924.answer: It depends on what exactly you did in the seminar papers. If no practical part in the form of, for example, data analyses or similar technical tools were used for the works, and it is, for example, pure literature research, unfortunately, this does not meet our requirements.

5e3a181f-1b71-437a-8ef1-6b50272aa49c.question: The system said that "we can only see the duration for one of your internships. Please also provide the duration for the other internship". Could the declaration of the second project would satisfy the demand of the proof of the project?

7906af68-65d0-4f45-8fca-9cb96ef73e0c.question: Does it have to be translated by an official translator? If I ask the university to sign an english translated version, would this suffice?
7906af68-65d0-4f45-8fca-9cb96ef73e0c.answer: Yes, your own translation + university signature would suffice for us.

97c82695-edf6-4cd2-88e7-356507870ad9.question: Based on my bachelor's degree, would I be a good fit for the AI in Society Master's Program at TUM?

0348fab8-5553-4964-97f8-910b35ce4eaa.question: May I know if there is a timeline on when we will be informed if we met all formal requirements, also on the final announcement itself?
0348fab8-5553-4964-97f8-910b35ce4eaa.answer: The test will be held online on June 25th. We will inform everyone about their admission to the test one week before the test at the latest. We will try our best to finish the decisions as early as possible.

e305fb7b-cec0-436f-b91c-642cd79c2595.question: Can I use my volunteer work in politics as proof of practical experience for the M. Sc. AI in Society program, even though I don't have a work certificate for it?

f6dac5da-b4eb-45c2-a288-11d54da1bd06.question: Can seminar papers be submitted as the practical part for the application to the AI in Society Master's program?

b626581c-139e-4939-ae82-3a171a54b713.question: What is the documentation requirement for the list of best 140 credits for the Master of Science AI in Society program?
b626581c-139e-4939-ae82-3a171a54b713.answer: For the list of 140 best credits, there will be a form to fill out inside the application portal. You will also be asked to upload your transcript of records.

59801068-f950-4e4f-acea-11dbf9e522f9.question: Are there any preparatory workshops or sessions offered by the university for the aptitude assessment for the Master of Science | AI in Society at TUM?

1fd3620a-ef0c-475e-ae8d-3eb964443ad3.question: Will the interviews for the AI in Society master's program at TUM be online or in person?
1fd3620a-ef0c-475e-ae8d-3eb964443ad3.answer: In case an interview is needed, there will be an option to do it online (if you are not able to come in person).

2f4eb85a-244c-42d4-9882-be7ea2b29012.question: What happens if the documents have not been received by uni-assist in full by the deadline?
2f4eb85a-244c-42d4-9882-be7ea2b29012.answer: If we then discover that your documents have not been received by [REDACTED] in full by the deadline, you will be excluded from the application process.

eecb5a0a-6532-41cb-98f1-636b1e3bf0b9.question: Which of the credits belonging to the [REDACTED] are counted for the 'practical project' requirement? Do these short descriptions of the [REDACTED] and the projects accomplished for the [REDACTED] courses seem to be fitting the 18 ECTS requirement?
eecb5a0a-6532-41cb-98f1-636b1e3bf0b9.answer: The 12 ECTS of the actual thesis project would count. Regarding the contents of your projects: they sound fitting. It does depend, however, if they incorporated a practical aspect with technical tools such as programming, statistical/data analysis, or similar. In case you decide to apply, please make sure to highlight such aspects in the project descriptions.

11406e7a-1d14-4b6f-bffa-97095de7278e.question: Do the projects accomplished for the [REDACTED] courses seem to be fitting the 18 ECTS requirement for the Master degree program 'AI in Society'?
11406e7a-1d14-4b6f-bffa-97095de7278e.answer: The contents of your projects sound fitting. In case you decide to apply, please make sure to highlight such aspects in the project descriptions.

b3413a63-6909-482b-a442-4da47118ada8.question: If I apply to this application cycle and get accepted, would it be possible to begin studies in summer semester 2025?
b3413a63-6909-482b-a442-4da47118ada8.answer: No, you could not start in the summer semester. You could, however, apply now, and accept the study place for winter semester 2025/26, in case you get admitted.

af466501-b8ce-4d09-9a73-356b3f4d137c.question: Can I use completed courses at university that were taught in English as English proof for the Master AI in Society program?
af466501-b8ce-4d09-9a73-356b3f4d137c.answer: In case you have completed courses at university that were taught in English, you can also use this as English proof.

64603168-34c2-46ca-a683-53906796299c.question: What can I do if I cannot afford another IELTS test and I only have 5 English-speaking credits passed?
64603168-34c2-46ca-a683-53906796299c.answer: You could try to get a certificate stating that you are currently attending English-speaking courses and their ECTS scope. Whether this will then be recognized as proof is not decided by me, but you could try that. Otherwise, I cannot offer you an alternative.

26388571-c03b-4447-ab14-7a2eb60b1bfc.question: How can an applicant prove the projects that they did in the courses for the AI in Society program application?
26388571-c03b-4447-ab14-7a2eb60b1bfc.answer: Applicants don't need to submit their project reports to prove completion of the module. Instead, they submit their Transcript of Records as part of the application procedure, as well as fill out a form which states the name of the project module, as well as the module/project description. For this, it is sufficient if they translate into English themselves.

756f5d59-bf68-4c39-be44-201bd1a45422.question: Is it problematic that we have set the aptitude test to be online-only, while the FPSO states that it is offered in person at TUM?
756f5d59-bf68-4c39-be44-201bd1a45422.answer: No, it is not problematic if we primarily offer the test as an online version (even if the FPSO states that it takes place in person). However, we must still offer an in-person test to people upon request, they have the right to it. For example, if someone is technically unable to take the test and only in-person is an option. We already have a room reserved for the test, we can simply keep it. If people report that they can only take the test in person, we will let them write the test on paper there.

6eda92e8-a43b-431c-95ee-f01232806036.question: What is the issue with candidate 1-00865541's application for the Mathe/[REDACTED]?
6eda92e8-a43b-431c-95ee-f01232806036.answer: The content of mathematics/statistics is unclear from the module titles alone. The candidate needs to provide some clarification, like official module descriptions, for these modules, to make apparent their relation to mathematics and/or statistics.

785f059a-6f4b-42da-b3d7-ad690630f77d.question: Can working experience be included to meet the ECTS requirement for the 'AI in Society' program at TUM?
785f059a-6f4b-42da-b3d7-ad690630f77d.answer: Yes, working experience can be included to reach the 18 ECTS requirement for the practical project.

6ecae05b-0970-45e9-8efb-27718649ad2b.question: Is it already fixed, the aptitude test will take place online?
6ecae05b-0970-45e9-8efb-27718649ad2b.answer: Yes, we are planning to make the test online.

80b45740-bf31-4c8d-9e0b-e6bdcbff6ad0.question: What should we do if an applicant cannot take the online test?
80b45740-bf31-4c8d-9e0b-e6bdcbff6ad0.answer: If an applicant cannot take the online test, we should let them take the test on paper at the reserved room.

7db0cced-4c9a-4280-9186-b49a5e9f353d.question: What can I do if I won't have my Capstone project phase 2 listed in my transcript by the application deadline (May 31st)?
7db0cced-4c9a-4280-9186-b49a5e9f353d.answer: If you will not have your Capstone project phase 2 listed in your transcript by May 31st, it could be a possibility to have your professor issue a letter, in which he verifies that you took the course, what you did in it, and how many ECTS the course spanned. The grade is not needed for us, we only need to know that you passed, and how many ECTS you earned from the course. This letter should then also have some type of university stamp on it.

1fd20a6d-0ca8-4d82-95e7-a3b02106ee01.question: At which stage and in what manner does the motivational letter influence the outcome of the application?
1fd20a6d-0ca8-4d82-95e7-a3b02106ee01.answer: The motivation letter is an optional element of your application. In case you are invited to an interview, your motivation letter can serve as the basis for the interview. Please don’t put crucial information like contents of your practical projects only in the motivation letter, as it will not be read unless you are invited to an interview.

2fe328c2-ff08-4b39-84dc-d5fe697dc21d.question: Is it problematic that the FPSO states the aptitude test is offered in presence at TUM, but we have now set it to be online-only?

caf0b415-9a4b-4612-862f-d6b5f66584de.question: When will the admission decisions be rendered and by when should applicants know if they are selected for an aptitude test?
caf0b415-9a4b-4612-862f-d6b5f66584de.answer: You will be notified whether or not you are invited to take the aptitude test at the very latest one week before the actual test (which is currently scheduled for June 25).

c85e9346-30bd-4a4e-a4c8-c1b0b36b76ab.question: What should I include in the form for practical projects inside the application portal?
c85e9346-30bd-4a4e-a4c8-c1b0b36b76ab.answer: In the form for practical projects, please write a clear and concise description of what exactly you accomplished in your capstone project. Make sure to highlight the practical and interdisciplinary aspects.

715703ce-a091-4210-8bee-11e5bdedcccd.question: Should I contact the lecturers to get some kind of text/letter, which states that the lectures were in English?

0da3ec07-0fef-4960-9eda-638bd32b723c.answer: I am forwarding you our degree program documentation, as it is a public document (but not to be found online yet). You can find information about the different modules in there.

cb93d38c-4b1a-4480-8720-c56a6e4e0b56.question: Could you please make the necessary correction in my application form?
cb93d38c-4b1a-4480-8720-c56a6e4e0b56.answer: I have forwarded this information. Everything is fine regarding your grades now, no need to worry.

3cef2974-9f1d-4bab-9609-6780506ef9b2.question: What should I do after completing the form to fill in the best credits?
3cef2974-9f1d-4bab-9609-6780506ef9b2.answer: You should upload it directly in the TUM Online application portal. The application portal will guide you through the documents you need to submit.

ec0fc1e8-f026-4c09-87fb-d75c4b5fc782.question: Is it recommended to combine working full-time with taking up a full-time Master’s degree?
ec0fc1e8-f026-4c09-87fb-d75c4b5fc782.answer: In general, we would not recommend trying to combine working full-time with taking up a full-time Master’s degree. The decision is, however, of course up to you.

fa1c8e8e-fa7a-49df-a7bb-741687237d1a.question: When will the admission decisions be rendered and by when should applicants know if they are selected for an aptitude test?
fa1c8e8e-fa7a-49df-a7bb-741687237d1a.answer: You will be notified whether or not you are invited to take the aptitude test at the very latest one week before the actual test, which is currently scheduled for June 25.

33a055b4-ddc6-49e2-961c-1637a734e9da.question: Can a course taught in English be considered as part of the English language proof?
33a055b4-ddc6-49e2-961c-1637a734e9da.answer: Yes, a course taught in English can be considered as part of the English language proof if the English Bachelor's thesis comes under 15 ECTS.

df7d49b5-e778-416a-9a18-4bd1b6978fe2.question: Is it worthwhile to apply for the masters in 'AI in Society' at TUM, given the professional experience of 1.5 years in the field of AI?
df7d49b5-e778-416a-9a18-4bd1b6978fe2.answer: Given your background, we of course welcome your application. Please make sure that you fulfil the prerequisites as listed on our website (i.e. credits from mathematics and/or statistics courses, practical experience.

f0fca572-1632-48b9-82ea-c28ff9d2073c.question: Do I need to obtain an official letter from the university confirming that the courses were taught in English, or is this information sufficient as proof of English proficiency for the M.Sc. AI in Society program at TUM?
f0fca572-1632-48b9-82ea-c28ff9d2073c.answer: To be formally correct, you should obtain an official statement that most of your degree was taught in English.

0ff8d221-d0d3-48e1-a2df-46b994f7c95f.question: How would I give the aptitude test in person for the 'AI in society' program as I'm not in Germany right now? Are there any online options available?
0ff8d221-d0d3-48e1-a2df-46b994f7c95f.answer: We are not yet sure if we are offering an online option. If the test will only be conducted in person, we are requiring the applicants to take the test in person.

ec95301d-11bc-4022-92ae-208cb22772a2.question: During the bachelor I had some courses that were called “Project”, so in total that makes 3 projects of 6 credits. Would it be posible to apply with 3 of them instead of 1 of 18 credits?
ec95301d-11bc-4022-92ae-208cb22772a2.answer: Yes, this is possible – please refer to our FAQ section: https://www.sot.tum.de/sot/studium/ai-in-society/application/

c9f6f6c1-9ae7-4984-afd4-effd68319b3c.question: When will more information on the aptitude test for the AI in Society course be released?
c9f6f6c1-9ae7-4984-afd4-effd68319b3c.answer: More information on the test will be released in the coming weeks.

eb933c85-2ae3-4c28-ba56-1803aa3d86b9.question: Is the aptitude test mandatory for all applicants?
eb933c85-2ae3-4c28-ba56-1803aa3d86b9.answer: Yes, the aptitude test is mandatory for all applicants who meet the formal requirements.

cdc48ba0-031d-4ff5-b669-f28d3a906fb9.question: What is the issue with my application for uni assist VPD as indicated in the attached screenshot?
cdc48ba0-031d-4ff5-b669-f28d3a906fb9.answer: You have indicated that you have applied for the VPD in full. Your proof of this has been received and provisionally OK. Please upload the final VPD for TUM here as soon as you receive it.
