ea930f1e-14a3-433d-9046-87d03383d77a.question: Is the aptitude test necessary for all applicants to the AI in Society program at TUM?
ea930f1e-14a3-433d-9046-87d03383d77a.answer: The aptitude test is mandatory for all applicants who have met the formal requirements. More detailed information about the test can be found on the TUM website.

7791ba28-90a6-4945-8732-8c707aedfb05.question: How would the practical project(for example the positive psychology program ) be counted as the ETCS? How would the time that I invested be counted? If I did it outside the university myself with the group of students?
7791ba28-90a6-4945-8732-8c707aedfb05.answer: 1 ECTS corresponds to 30 hours of work. So, for example, if you tell us that you worked for one month, we would calculate a 40-hour work week (or 20-hour if part-time is stated), times 4 weeks. In this case, it would be 160 hours. 160 hours would correspond to 5,3 ECTS. In any case, you need to provide to us some kind of statement (as I described in the previous email), from the positive psychology program you participated in.

bd985b91-50a7-40c5-9efb-31038152dda2.question: I want to apply for MSC AI in Society at TUM and meet all the requirements but I have a bit of clutter regarding the point 'a practical project worth at least 18 credits completed during the bachelor’s studies.' My project phase 2 will be completed by 1st May 2024 which suffices this requirement but its APS verified transcripts won't be available before the TUM application deadline ends. Can I apply with the phase one APS verified results and give the phase 2 results as soon as they are available?
bd985b91-50a7-40c5-9efb-31038152dda2.answer: We need to have all of your documents by the application deadline (May 31st), we cannot make exceptions. If you will not have your Capstone project phase 2 listed in your transcript by May 31st, it could be a possibility to have your professor issue a letter, in which he verifies that you took the course, what you did in it, and how many ECTS the course spanned. The grade is not needed for us, we only need to know that you passed, and how many ECTS you earned from the course. This letter should then also have some type of university stamp on it.

252cf0db-5051-476d-a610-8ec9536657c5.question: Is there a specific form for the declaration that needs to be signed at the end of the motivational letter for the Msc in AI in Society application at TUM?
252cf0db-5051-476d-a610-8ec9536657c5.answer: There is no specific form. Please simply state at the bottom of your motivational letter, in your own words, that you have written the letter yourself and without external help.

42c11aea-068f-494b-8574-a69bc4509246.question: What should I do if my Capstone project phase 2 is not listed in my transcript by the application deadline?
42c11aea-068f-494b-8574-a69bc4509246.answer: If you will not have your Capstone project phase 2 listed in your transcript by May 31st, it could be a possibility to have your professor issue a letter, in which he verifies that you took the course, what you did in it, and how many ECTS the course spanned. The grade is not needed for us, we only need to know that you passed, and how many ECTS you earned from the course. This letter should then also have some type of university stamp on it.

fb11dace-b998-4a9f-bedb-326945e1aaac.question: Which programs am I eligible to apply for at your university? Does the tuition fee for a program affect the admissions difficulty?
fb11dace-b998-4a9f-bedb-326945e1aaac.answer: I cannot provide you general information on other TUM study programs. For this, I would kindly refer you to TUM’s student information center: https://www.tum.de/en/studies/support-and-advice/support-during-studies/student-information.

4c93ee38-b77b-471c-8b93-c501e1f4af3f.question: How would the duration and ECTS be considered for this project?
4c93ee38-b77b-471c-8b93-c501e1f4af3f.answer: If this project was part of your studies (i.e. it is listed on your Transcript of Records), this is sufficient as proof. We will refer to the credits given to the module (and convert to ECTS if your credit system is not based on ECTS). If you participated in this project outside of university, i.e. it is not listed on your Transcript, then we need another form of proof. For example, if this was an internship or a work experience, we ask you to upload a work certificate issued by the place where you worked on this project. It should state exactly what you did there, and how long you were involved.

5e7225f1-8c5a-4784-8589-7640f3fcf298.question: What should I include in the form for practical projects?
5e7225f1-8c5a-4784-8589-7640f3fcf298.answer: In the form for practical projects, please write a clear and concise description of what exactly you accomplished in your capstone project. Make sure to highlight the practical and interdisciplinary aspects.

a1778823-a4fa-4764-bc1f-80b075d6c463.question: What happens if the APS for WiSe 24/25 including the other required certificates is not in Berlin by the deadline of 31.05.24?
a1778823-a4fa-4764-bc1f-80b075d6c463.answer: If this is not the case, a VPD can still be issued at some point, but it can then no longer be taken into account for WiSe 24/25.

75ac2d8e-3cf2-45f3-8bc4-3d27adec71e0.question: Do you know someone whom I could contact about the management of the application?

9a777865-8679-45fb-b737-8feff9928601.question: Since when do you offer this program?
9a777865-8679-45fb-b737-8feff9928601.answer: The first time we are offering this program will be the coming winter semester 2024/25. This is a new program. However, many of the courses taught as part of the program are established modules at TUM.

d94b8b9d-228b-40c1-ae8f-2a1fb8829a7c.question: What should a work certificate for the AI in Society master's program at TUM look like?
d94b8b9d-228b-40c1-ae8f-2a1fb8829a7c.answer: There is no strict form on work certificates. Normally they are letters handed out by your (previous) employer, summarizing what the employee (you) did at their company (e.g. for reference for the person’s future employer). It should simply state what your role was at the company, which type of work you did, which projects you participated in, as well as the duration of your employment with them. It should be evident to us that you didn’t write the letter yourself, i.e. the employer/their HR department could sign at the bottom, have their logo on the letter, or similar.

97ac5b48-868a-4747-b78a-f4b597b57134.question: Can the APS application form and payment receipt be enough proof to initiate my application?

e9d5db75-d557-4b1a-b0e1-fbf1e8a3282c.question: What is the VPD requirement for the application to TUM?
e9d5db75-d557-4b1a-b0e1-fbf1e8a3282c.answer: The VPD checks your university documents. It is stated as a requirement on TUM's websites.

b3d1867c-f934-4a13-9552-401cd5a90259.question: If from my university, I do not officially have 18 credits for a practical project in social science, is there a way to make up for this requirement?
b3d1867c-f934-4a13-9552-401cd5a90259.answer: Unfortunately, as much as we would want to, we can't just let you compile an own project without an official documentation about how much time was spent for it. Please understand that we need to compare students' achievements universally somehow; this we can do by setting a minimum of ECTS credits, or, hours invested.

e8324065-adff-48aa-97c4-01f3f68a1d3f.question: Can the project be part of a course or does it have to stand individually?
e8324065-adff-48aa-97c4-01f3f68a1d3f.answer: The email does not provide a clear answer to this question. NO ANSWER.

5c44957c-de75-435d-9a86-aa382db62830.question: What should I include in the form for practical projects in the application portal?
5c44957c-de75-435d-9a86-aa382db62830.answer: In the form for practical projects, please write a clear and concise description of what exactly you accomplished in your capstone project. Make sure to highlight the practical and interdisciplinary aspects.

b830a19a-3a60-4765-ac01-0a60390eb0ed.question: Can you provide all details for the AI M.Sc. program as per my specific case?

affe26e5-bff7-4cd4-ae4e-8d475ba1975f.question: For the “Evidence of English”, I have already been checked with IELTS when I apply for the RCI master program, how can I fulfill this requirement automatically?
affe26e5-bff7-4cd4-ae4e-8d475ba1975f.answer: In this case, please upload the same IELTS certificate again in your application to AI in Society.

a4b389b6-6e86-43bf-afea-d1cc2aa963ed.question: Can I upload employment verification from my employer for the practical experience, in lieu of the 18 credit hours in undergrad?

09488df5-9458-44a2-b1c8-70b4d9b74d88.question: What is the requirement for the letter issued by the professor?
09488df5-9458-44a2-b1c8-70b4d9b74d88.answer: The letter issued by your professor should verify that you took the course, what you did in it, and how many ECTS the course spanned. The grade is not needed, only the information that you passed, and how many ECTS you earned from the course. This letter should also have some type of university stamp on it.

70b5dbd0-757b-42b2-a0e7-3c2de56fd550.question: What should be referred to for the 'best 140 ECTS' in the form?
70b5dbd0-757b-42b2-a0e7-3c2de56fd550.answer: For the 'best 140 ECTS', please refer to your bachelor’s transcript.

071bf987-0559-4624-9efc-968d6b95383c.question: For the “Evidence of English”, I have already been checked with IELTS when I apply for the RCI master program, how can I fullfill this requirement automatically?
071bf987-0559-4624-9efc-968d6b95383c.answer: In this case, please upload the same IELTS certificate again in your application to AI in Society.

3cc4099d-646a-4c2f-88a2-d4e642e3161b.question: Is the grade of the practical project required for the application to the MSC AI in Society at TUM?
3cc4099d-646a-4c2f-88a2-d4e642e3161b.answer: No, the grade is not needed. The application only needs to know that the course was passed and how many ECTS were earned from it.

748f4496-1c08-4831-9f01-c724932bb9a8.question: Does the university accept the result of the IELTS single subject having the 'retake' logo in one transcript or the result of the component of two tests?
748f4496-1c08-4831-9f01-c724932bb9a8.answer: This should be fine, but it is advised to also add an explanation when uploading this document (for example, add another page at the very beginning, where you write this explanation). Otherwise, it will not be clear.

a24d1971-a8ca-48e6-b517-a9dde1a6c0f8.question: Is it acceptable to provide the certificate for the MIT ADSP Capstone Project after the application deadline?
a24d1971-a8ca-48e6-b517-a9dde1a6c0f8.answer: If you can provide the certificate until the application deadline (May 31st), it will be fine.

63710851-b85e-437a-9923-80ffebdc4430.question: Can my real working experiences demonstrate my project management skills instead of a practical project relevant to the course of study within at least 18 credits including module description?

181e9aad-8da8-4cec-a9bf-d0d47c377715.question: Would I be exempt from tuition fees or required to pay if my bachelor’s degree was obtained from my home country outside of the EU/EEA, but I have lived, studied, and worked in Germany for almost 4 years during my master’s studies?

0c8ed349-2fbc-4419-9851-340d4e8a4e07.question: Can practical experience gained through extracurricular internships or work experience be considered for the MSc. AI in Society program at TUM?

6af04d35-ade3-4d10-bb38-4a0b0b5f53d0.question: How can I fill in my courses equivalent to 140 credits if the given form is not enough?
6af04d35-ade3-4d10-bb38-4a0b0b5f53d0.answer: Duplicate the form, fill out however many fields you need, merge the documents back into one, and upload it like this.

e9975f7d-891e-44e3-9e5e-c421dacfca1a.question: Can I apply to the Masters program in AI in society at TUM if I have not yet completed my Bachelor's degree?
e9975f7d-891e-44e3-9e5e-c421dacfca1a.answer: Yes, you can apply to the study program even if you still haven’t finished your Bachelors degree. Instead, you should submit your current Transcript of Records, which should span at least 140 ECTS credits. However, you will need to submit your final Bachelors certificate if you get admitted to the study program.

85e54b21-8714-4ed4-865a-996ff0d3c412.question: If I filled all the tables of the document, but it didn't reach the requirement of 140 ECT in total, can I duplicate the table and add courses to let the total number of credits of all courses listed reach 140 ECT?
85e54b21-8714-4ed4-865a-996ff0d3c412.answer: Yes, if there is not enough space, you can duplicate the form.

bb3fcb5a-463e-4fed-a6b4-5510e3f0e350.question: Will the content of the courses I list in the 'List of 140 best credits' document affect the outcome of my application?
bb3fcb5a-463e-4fed-a6b4-5510e3f0e350.answer: This will affect your application only in a good way: we're asking for this sorting, because we only consider your best grades for calculating your admission score. This form is essentially just some help for us to see right away, which of your modules are your best, without manually sorting through your Transcript of Records.

a5c3f2a1-f6e8-4817-9561-eb0a75dbc8cf.question: What documents are required if I want to submit work experience/internships/etc. for the practical project for the MSc. AI in Society program?
a5c3f2a1-f6e8-4817-9561-eb0a75dbc8cf.answer: If you want to submit work experience/internships/etc., we would need a work certificate that shows: a) what you did there in terms of content, and b) how long the relationship lasted.

d0634c91-c1ac-4f8b-a8fc-3e177086a4dc.question: Can an English Bachelor's thesis be used as proof of English proficiency in the AIS application?
d0634c91-c1ac-4f8b-a8fc-3e177086a4dc.answer: Yes, an English Bachelor's thesis can be used as proof of English proficiency in the AIS application.

5a2fbb8d-8ced-4fac-aa25-d0e14e55f3d5.question: What should be done if the document uploaded in the application portal cannot be considered as English language proof for the AI and Society Master's program?
5a2fbb8d-8ced-4fac-aa25-d0e14e55f3d5.answer: If you want to count your Bachelor's thesis as proof instead, please upload either a) a corresponding transcript (see above), or b) a separate certificate from the university at this point.

3c65c5b0-7fd4-4585-8248-baa0980a67f2.question: Are my internships at KPMG, HBplus, 3T.Law, and a pending internship at WTS appropriate in terms of their content for the Master's program AI in Society?

03cc20ef-4ff6-49af-a484-da5e1f8147c3.question: Do I need a Toefl test, as the Abitur with B2 level is not enough, right?

163c3b2f-c753-4144-9d0b-ab8fa010c68e.question: Do I fulfill the requirement of the practical project worth at least 18 ECTS or can I make up for it during the course of my studies?
163c3b2f-c753-4144-9d0b-ab8fa010c68e.answer: Your total 7 months of internships/jobs would cover the requirement of the practical project worth at least 18 ECTS. However, the content of your practical experiences is also important. We are looking for interdisciplinarity in the applicant’s project(s) and strongly require a practical aspect in the form of implementation(programming), some kind of data analysis, or similar, applied to some sort of field in society.

f8c122de-47f4-4929-b190-d6decd25d4cb.question: What should I do if the document I uploaded as proof of English proficiency is not accepted?
f8c122de-47f4-4929-b190-d6decd25d4cb.answer: If the document you uploaded cannot be considered as proof of English proficiency, please upload either a) a corresponding transcript (as described above), or b) a separate certificate from the university.

225a6f32-c880-4382-88cc-0a91860778a5.question: Is a Bachelor's thesis written in English sufficient as a language proficiency proof for the AI and Society Master's program?
225a6f32-c880-4382-88cc-0a91860778a5.answer: For the AI in Society program, a Bachelor's thesis written in English is also sufficient as proof of language proficiency.

e30b9a18-4399-4f9c-ba10-da8ee33eb300.question: Regarding the Math and Statistics portion of submitting my documents, I received an email saying it was incorrect, however I am uncertain how to correct it.
e30b9a18-4399-4f9c-ba10-da8ee33eb300.answer: The portal says: “Please list only academic achievements in mathematics” as the issue. And looking at your filled out form, you have indeed listed modules such as economics. The issue doesn’t seem to have anything to do with the modules stemming from your Masters degree. If you fix this and re-upload the form, it should be fine.

21387d7f-194b-487a-9a23-7404e74d0647.question: What is the procedure for verifying if the modules that applicants indicate really correspond to at least 5 ECTS for Math/Statistics and 18 ECTS for a practical project?

1c8d5db6-02dc-4e33-b095-e8ea7a5abb38.question: How do we verify if the modules that applicants indicate really correspond to at least 5 ECTS for Math/Statistics and 18 ECTS for the Practical Project?

9cd69651-625e-406b-bd26-740900ad6f06.question: Is the list of best credits different from a transcript? Do I need to provide this?
9cd69651-625e-406b-bd26-740900ad6f06.answer: In the application form, there will be a separate form for you to fill in your list of best 140 ECTS credits. This is simply some help for us in order to calculate your aptitude score, where we only consider (a fraction of) your grades during your studies, i.e. the best ones. So, yes, this is different from your official transcript, which lists all your modules. You’re correct, AI in Society is indeed not listed as one of the programs asking for this document.

cdc6692d-d6e8-4438-b6e8-5a71e4978e9c.question: Can I include my research paper on meat production analysis as part of the proof for the completed practical project requirement for the M.Sc. AI in Society application?
cdc6692d-d6e8-4438-b6e8-5a71e4978e9c.answer: Yes, if there was some practical/implementation aspect included (i.e. it was not a literature review kind of paper, but you actually ran some analysis yourself), it would make sense to include this.

e6685480-e692-4fb9-90ef-7dbcbd40e48e.question: Is it possible to credit my professional experience for the 'practical project' requirement?
e6685480-e692-4fb9-90ef-7dbcbd40e48e.answer: You should indicate your work-student activity in the 'Practical Project' section when applying. For non-ECTS-based experiences (i.e., professional experience), we ask applicants to submit a work certificate or similar documentation. It must be clear to us: a) what the applicant has dealt with in terms of content, and b) the period in which the employment relationship existed (we roughly convert to hours. 1 ECTS corresponds to approx. 30h. Your missing 2 ECTS should be easily covered).

58be7729-bcd4-4ef2-9b03-3503e7216dcf.question: In the requirements for the MSc. AI in Society, it is mentioned that applicants should have completed a practical project worth at least 18 credits during their bachelor’s studies. Would I still be eligible for this program if the sum of my completed modules would meet the required 18 credit points?
58be7729-bcd4-4ef2-9b03-3503e7216dcf.answer: Yes, you are free to submit multiple practical modules which in sum make up 18 ECTS. The wording is a bit confusing, leading people to think that we require one single project worth 18 credits.

19d6bfbd-ecfb-47d9-8c23-b84bc2bb862b.question: Is it possible to arrange a short phone call next week or are there office hours where I can visit you in the department at TU?

8b241f43-512c-4728-bd81-b7e22e0888c3.question: Can TUM consider my internship experience gained during my Masters degree and/or my six (6) plus years of professional experience working for the Department of Transportation as a in lieu of these 18 ECTS credit hours?
8b241f43-512c-4728-bd81-b7e22e0888c3.answer: Yes, it is possible to provide evidence of practical experience that was not gained as part of your studies, but rather as working experience or similar. In this case, please provide us some documents (like a certificate of employment), which indicates to us: a) the content of your work, and b) the duration (18 ECTS are equivalent to 540 hours of work). Same thing applies to your internship experience.

6b630afe-99d5-4578-a251-ea6086858851.question: How can one participate in the VR study?
6b630afe-99d5-4578-a251-ea6086858851.answer: Interested participants should send an email to the provided address expressing their desire to participate. Participation will be determined based on availability.

c6c06db8-a2ee-4c62-b122-664bcfc548bc.question: Will the mistake in the application number impact the application?

ef35fca9-59d0-4134-9a21-98385b71d94f.question: Does a course titled 'Introduction to AI (5 ECTS)' and a Bachelor's thesis on AI chatbots, focusing on their various use cases (15 ECTS), meet the criteria for the practical project requirement for the TUM M.Sc. program 'AI in Society'?
ef35fca9-59d0-4134-9a21-98385b71d94f.answer: The final decision is subject to the aptitude committee. However, judging from your description, it should be fine topic-wise.

aadcd37c-2ab6-47f2-93df-95478361abe7.question: What should be selected for the 'Übertragungsweg der Rechnung' and 'Email address for digital invoice' fields when creating an entry for the 'International Programmes in Germany 2024/25' database?
aadcd37c-2ab6-47f2-93df-95478361abe7.answer: For the 'Übertragungsweg der Rechnung', 'no' should be selected. The 'Email address for digital invoice' field can be left blank as the data for all basic entries will be entered on 03.05.

50cf2308-19e5-4c55-b7bc-f561afd5ffe5.question: What is the cost for publishing in the 'International Programmes in Germany 2024/25' database?
50cf2308-19e5-4c55-b7bc-f561afd5ffe5.answer: The cost for publishing in the 'International Programmes in Germany 2024/25' database is 100 Euros for basic entries and 600 Euros for premium entries with images, videos, etc.

ae27282d-19cc-4329-8539-88f65a45969e.question: Do I need to enter anything for 'Übertragungsweg der Rechnung' and 'Email address for digital invoice'?
ae27282d-19cc-4329-8539-88f65a45969e.answer: You need to enter something, otherwise you cannot release the entry.

c15126bb-4850-47cd-9f6a-cb42f50b027a.question: I completed one internship during my bachelors studies. However, is it possible / would TUM consider my internship experience gained during my Masters degree and/or my six (6) plus years of professional experience working for the [REDACTED] Department of Transportation as a [REDACTED] in lieu of these 18 ECTS credit hours?
c15126bb-4850-47cd-9f6a-cb42f50b027a.answer: Yes, it is possible to provide evidence of practical experience that was not gained as part of your studies, but rather as working experience or similar. In this case, please provide us some documents (like a certificate of employment), which indicates to us: a) the content of your work, and b) the duration (18 ECTS are equivalent to 540 hours of work). Same thing applies to your internship experience.

d00e9c01-d344-4056-8029-378704f0a405.question: What is the procedure to verify if the modules that people specify really correspond to at least 5 or 18 ECTS for the requirements of '5 ECTS Math/Statistics' and '18 ECTS Practical Project' respectively?

8571090d-9793-4221-888d-07daca2650af.question: Shouldn't the status of the document initially be 'received' instead of 'ok', since we would have to check it first?

4f3c90b3-509f-4143-8f36-ba77d2ccc611.question: Is the AIS study programme accredited or registered for accreditation?

caf2b543-53df-4d29-b917-02a9d77718d8.question: What is the request regarding the five-year program for architecture students?
caf2b543-53df-4d29-b917-02a9d77718d8.answer: The applicant requests that the five-year program for architecture students be considered when reviewing their application materials.

7b001e5d-3117-433b-a9b8-f6d94fde57e6.question: Is it possible to submit an application for the AI in Society master’s program before completing the APS process and obtaining the VPD certificate, and provide these documents at a later stage?
7b001e5d-3117-433b-a9b8-f6d94fde57e6.answer: No, incomplete applications cannot be accepted, and applicants cannot submit certain documents after the deadline (May 31) has passed.

42481fca-4ed5-49b2-8336-03a42c2d2291.question: How does the timetable look for the AI in Society master's program at TUM? Is it only classes in the morning or only classes in the evening, or a mix?
42481fca-4ed5-49b2-8336-03a42c2d2291.answer: The scheduling is up to the professors and many courses are not set up yet, since the degree program is under active construction at the moment. It cannot be confirmed whether the courses will be rather in the morning or rather in the evening.

75b87594-f139-4b6e-9977-dd07c19ea99b.question: Is there any further information on how the admission test is structured and what questions can be expected?
75b87594-f139-4b6e-9977-dd07c19ea99b.answer: For now, you can refer to the rough topics that can be found on our website (https://www.sot.tum.de/sot/studium/ai-in-society/application/). We will try our best to publish more in-depth information surrounding the test as soon as we can.

f9c9c226-f58a-4c2d-87aa-fdeee1052ce5.question: Where can I find more information about scholarships at TUM?
f9c9c226-f58a-4c2d-87aa-fdeee1052ce5.answer: Regarding scholarships, I would kindly redirect you to TUM’s scholarship office. For more information and their contact, please see here: https://www.tum.de/en/studies/fees-and-financial-aid/scholarships

9d08eea5-d33d-4a3c-a70b-b0cd726fc911.question: Will my age be an issue for application to the Master in AI in Society program at TUM?
9d08eea5-d33d-4a3c-a70b-b0cd726fc911.answer: Your age is definitely not a problem in any way.

17f112ae-47f2-4b0a-b49e-ae931eae8077.question: Can I apply for the M.Sc. AI in Society program at TUM if I don't have a bachelor's thesis or a project with credits, but have extensive work experience?
17f112ae-47f2-4b0a-b49e-ae931eae8077.answer: Yes, you can prove your practical expertise through work experience. This might include working on projects relevant to the study field during your employment. However, you will need to submit suitable proof for this, such as a certificate of employment. The proof of practical experience needs to indicate how much time you spent on it, and it should correspond to the 18 ECTS requirement of the program. It also has to be clear what exactly you were working on.

e1d2b606-87b1-4948-9ab6-6980c04f41ea.question: Can you provide further information about the application process for the M.Sc. AI in Society program?
e1d2b606-87b1-4948-9ab6-6980c04f41ea.answer: More information about the application process can be found on the website: https://www.sot.tum.de/sot/studium/ai-in-society/application/. For an extensive overview over the required application documents and procedure, please see here: https://www.tum.de/studium/studienangebot/detail/ai-in-society.

50d0a13c-7082-4f97-aca5-c016793f8d1e.question: [REDACTED] courses taken in bachelor degree studies replace IELTS or TOEFL? For example; Is it sufficient to have taken 21 ECTS credits in English for applying to this program?
50d0a13c-7082-4f97-aca5-c016793f8d1e.answer: Please find the relevant information here under “Verification of [REDACTED] by Language of Instruction”: https://www.tum.de/en/studies/application/application-info-portal/admission-requirements/language-certificates

a1f11620-6214-4689-a2b2-9e10b45e5477.question: What should I do about the VPD requirement in my application?
a1f11620-6214-4689-a2b2-9e10b45e5477.answer: You have indicated that you have applied for the VPD in full. Your proof of this has been received and provisionally OK. The document is now only set to 'not OK' so that you can upload the final VPD here. Uni-assist will email you the final VPD once it is complete. Please upload the final VPD for TUM here as soon as you receive it. However, if we then discover that your documents have not been received by [REDACTED] in full by the deadline, you will be excluded from the application process. Depending on how old your previous VPD is, you can submit it here again (we accept VPDs that are up to 3 years old). Otherwise, you must submit a new VPD.

e0d63516-ca0b-4170-971f-42e1c687ed89.question: Can applicants submit proof of practical experience in the form of their Bachelor's thesis if it is not completed at the time of application?
e0d63516-ca0b-4170-971f-42e1c687ed89.answer: No, it is not intended that examination achievements from the Bachelor's degree, which are only completed after the application deadline, can be submitted later.

28678f0b-22bb-4adc-b312-80394d560be2.question: Can practical experience outside of the degree program be considered for the M.Sc. AI in Society program application?
28678f0b-22bb-4adc-b312-80394d560be2.answer: Yes, practical experience outside of your degree program can be considered. This might include work at a company during your studies, where you were working on projects relevant to the study field. However, suitable proof for this, such as a certificate of employment, needs to be submitted.

27d2657b-0854-43f1-96b1-c2e386a4b2e1.question: Is it possible to arrange a short phone call or visit the department at TU to discuss the program and the admission process?

33c15b1b-2f76-44dd-b432-8ffd87e8b8c5.question: Would a weekly research & review work also count as a project in the requirement?

25cb2cdf-294b-40d5-8464-6481d2d11ebe.question: Can I make up for the missing 6 ECTS through professional experience or other relevant (extracurricular) activities?
25cb2cdf-294b-40d5-8464-6481d2d11ebe.answer: You may be able to prove the missing 6 ECTS through professional experience or other relevant (extracurricular) activities.

f927bedf-17dd-4e66-b4f1-db6f9cbb801f.question: Can I be exempted from submitting an English proficiency certificate for the M.Sc. AI in Society program if I studied in the UK for the last year of my double degree bachelor program and obtained 60 ECTS including the bachelor's thesis?
f927bedf-17dd-4e66-b4f1-db6f9cbb801f.answer: If your degree’s language of instruction was English, you do not have to submit additional proof of English proficiency.

c13e0ec7-b6c2-453f-be6b-423774fff301.question: How should grades from a diploma degree be considered in the application process for the AI in Society program at TUM?
c13e0ec7-b6c2-453f-be6b-423774fff301.answer: In case of doubt, the overall average grade should be used for the points for the grade (Annex 2, No. 5.1.1 a) Sentence 10).

52a5ce60-b4af-454a-a777-8b5c1237ee73.question: Is it possible to arrange a short phone call next week or are there office hours where I can visit you in the department at TU?

e38194fd-1476-41ff-9a5f-b80b556c12f3.question: Do you have the dates more or less when it will happen?
e38194fd-1476-41ff-9a5f-b80b556c12f3.answer: Exact dates are not available, but it is expected to happen mid-June. The exact date will be communicated at least one week in advance.

9c6f7dab-88c9-4711-bb07-9daec0fd8a1c.question: What should I do if the document for listing undergraduate modules does not provide enough space for all my modules?
9c6f7dab-88c9-4711-bb07-9daec0fd8a1c.answer: You should download the document twice and use the extra rows from the second copy. Then upload both forms. It would be great if you could fuse the two documents into one PDF before uploading.

19350bba-6ef7-4d29-9223-abb8ba713adc.question: How long more or less does it take to get an answer in the application?
19350bba-6ef7-4d29-9223-abb8ba713adc.answer: Applications are reviewed on a rolling basis. If something is missing in your application, you will be contacted again. If everything is fine, you will also get informed. This might happen over the next 2-3 weeks.

7809ca70-c5cc-4d81-a462-b03419a13250.question: Do I need to go through the college for one year to have access to the course or do I have access directly to it from my current situation?
7809ca70-c5cc-4d81-a462-b03419a13250.answer: You need to apply with a Bachelor’s degree. If during the application period (until May 31st) you will not have finished your bachelor’s degree yet, 140 ECTS credits of your Bachelor’s studies are sufficient, assuming that you will finish your Bachelor’s degree still before the start of the Master’s.

a8b2f945-a603-4a44-8640-7b6c2c0f2ee4.question: Do I fulfill the requirement for the practical project for the M.Sc. AI in Society at TUM if I sum all of the credits for which I had a project and it is over 18 ECTS?
a8b2f945-a603-4a44-8640-7b6c2c0f2ee4.answer: You should submit the entire modules as proof for the practical project requirement. Your case might become a question for the admission committee to decide upon. For now, count the entire modules containing those practical projects inside of them.

7432d446-626d-44e3-ae0e-fdb44097d791.question: Can a bachelor's thesis in the field of data analysis, which is worth 12 ECTS, be recognized as equivalent to the 'practical project' requirement of at least 18 credits for the AI in Society master's program?
7432d446-626d-44e3-ae0e-fdb44097d791.answer: The bachelor's thesis can be counted towards the practical project requirement, but as it only covers 12 ECTS, it is not entirely sufficient. Additional practical-oriented modules from the bachelor's program or relevant experience outside of studies, if properly documented, can be used to cover the remaining 6 ECTS. For example, if the experience is from a relevant part-time student job, an employment certificate would be a good proof. To cover the missing 6 ECTS, a proof that this experience has covered at least 6x30h = 180h is required, along with a description of this project.

eb8fa0d1-795a-4527-b58c-5b905853e828.question: Could you send me a link of the website that doesn’t work for you?
eb8fa0d1-795a-4527-b58c-5b905853e828.answer: The website link that doesn’t work is https://www.sot.tum.de/en/sot/404-notfound-sot-en/.

0aa8dbae-b62d-4009-8711-38f02ad8bd69.question: What happens when the website page showing the additional admission requirements doesn't work?
0aa8dbae-b62d-4009-8711-38f02ad8bd69.answer: If the website page showing the additional admission requirements doesn't work, you can reach out for assistance and you will be provided with working links that contain all relevant information.

dd092991-f5fa-4785-9065-e702ea706b88.question: Where can I find the list of the admission requirements for the AI and society master?

f95058a8-b952-48ce-805b-39b113e755a0.question: Do the attached transcripts fulfil the minimum requirements of mathematics/statistics background?
f95058a8-b952-48ce-805b-39b113e755a0.answer: No, the attached transcripts do not fulfil the minimum requirements of mathematics/statistics background.

24f14a52-21a3-4bb1-8308-abb7f1bad1a2.question: Is it possible to use multiple practical projects (each 4-8 ECTS) as valid proof if they together are ≥ 18 ECTS?
24f14a52-21a3-4bb1-8308-abb7f1bad1a2.answer: Yes, it does not have to be a single project over 18 ECTS, it can also be accumulated from several projects.

f17141df-4f06-474f-94c4-c5359df9fa40.question: Can you please tell where I can find the list of the admission requirements for this master?

aaa7eb8c-c9d1-473b-871e-2c7ded7bd65f.question: How does the aptitude committee assess practical experience for the AI in Society program at TUM?
aaa7eb8c-c9d1-473b-871e-2c7ded7bd65f.answer: The aptitude committee decides if an applicant has suitable/sufficient practical experience. Applicants should submit evidence of their work, such as employment references.

1945f729-e121-4bf4-8bd6-d4599c9b4f50.question: If from my university, I do not officially have 18 credits for a practical project in social science, is there a way to make up for this requirement?
1945f729-e121-4bf4-8bd6-d4599c9b4f50.answer: Yes, by providing official documentation of practical projects that in total spanned at least 540 hours for completion.

5080b9fe-0dc3-4b26-a313-668f814b87c1.question: What should I do if my foreign university's courses are not provided in the form of modules and I have more courses than the provided rows in the 'List of best 140 Credits' form for the 'AI in Society' master program application?
5080b9fe-0dc3-4b26-a313-668f814b87c1.answer: You can download the respective form two times to fill in all your courses, then mark which is the first, and which is the second (e.g. insert “1” and “2” somewhere on the PDF), and upload both of them. You may need to merge these two PDFs back into one.

2ee45adf-f0ec-4921-9c43-ede9cbe36c25.question: Is the original thesis document, accompanied by an English introduction summarizing it, sufficient as proof of the project's completion for the M.Sc. AI in Society application?
2ee45adf-f0ec-4921-9c43-ede9cbe36c25.answer: You do not need to submit your thesis for the application. For proof, you will have to provide your Transcript of Records when you’re applying. This module should also be listed there.

71dcc55c-eda0-4643-b938-48021fb98e4f.question: Is there any additional material or information that I should provide?

383f417c-40a2-44ed-9c72-7a371a5b67a8.question: If I am eligible for a waiver of the English proficiency certificate, would it be necessary for my university to provide a document verifying that English was the language of instruction during my Master's studies?
383f417c-40a2-44ed-9c72-7a371a5b67a8.answer: If you wish to submit a confirmation of your language of instruction as proof of your English language proficiency, the confirmation has to be issued by an administrative unit of the university on official university paper and has to bear a seal and an original signature.

52afc1cd-288d-43f4-a487-3cb49595eb62.question: What kind of proof is needed to verify the hours spent on a practical project for the AI for society program?
52afc1cd-288d-43f4-a487-3cb49595eb62.answer: A credible documentation of practical experience is important. Verifiable documents that confirm content and scope should be able to be presented.

7b1ecfac-ab57-45da-b865-4f489f186896.question: Are there any recommended books or references to help prepare for the aptitude test for the Master's Program in AI in Society?

206afa59-6d7d-49aa-b78e-1527c60b24f8.question: Who will send the link to the application portal for the MSc. AI in Society program?
206afa59-6d7d-49aa-b78e-1527c60b24f8.answer: Ms. [REDACTED] will send a link to the application portal.

94737c9d-a97e-430c-a6a9-31d9d507dfae.question: If from my university, I do not officially 18 credits for a practical project in social science, is there a way to make up for this requirement?

27f998aa-3d33-4efa-a07d-b42bf215c804.question: What does the requirement of 'List of [REDACTED]' mean for the M.Sc. AI in Society program application?
27f998aa-3d33-4efa-a07d-b42bf215c804.answer: The 'List of [REDACTED]' requirement asks you to submit your best 140 ECTS credits, meaning, listing the modules where you got the best grades, overall worth 140 credits. The information about 90 credits is referring to something different and is not relevant for this Master’s.

2f6ab7c7-0926-4f9c-b45e-669377fd1283.question: What are the requirements for the practical project for the MSc. AI in Society application?
2f6ab7c7-0926-4f9c-b45e-669377fd1283.answer: If you have completed at least 18 ECTS (your bachelor's thesis can also be counted) in a/multiple practical project(s), which involve a) some sort of technical tools and b) some societal aspect, we highly encourage you to apply. If you have the 18 ECTS, but aren't quite sure if the topics of your projects fit perfectly, please apply regardless.

51bc9584-5698-4a69-8ad8-14411e261b58.question: Does the student have the 18 Credits needed in practical projects for the application for the MSc. AI in Society?

1c2662cf-db08-4a7a-a7f8-44b85a8ad659.question: Would you be available for a short meeting this week or the coming?

d6b8d0df-005c-458e-a198-bed0e146f1fc.question: If I don't have the project that you are inquiring about, is it worthy giving it a try to the application?
d6b8d0df-005c-458e-a198-bed0e146f1fc.answer: If you have completed projects during your studies that are roughly in the field we describe (even if not matching perfectly), we highly encourage you to apply.

f6385dd3-7d88-4954-ab5a-d32e21f4f41a.question: What is required to submit when applying for the AI in Society program?
f6385dd3-7d88-4954-ab5a-d32e21f4f41a.answer: Submitting your bachelor’s transcript of records is mandatory, and the best 140 ECTS credits based on your bachelor’s degree will be counted.

850e310b-dc26-4581-88a6-179568e24926.question: Can my bachelor's and master's theses be considered as practical projects for the AI in Society program at TUM?
850e310b-dc26-4581-88a6-179568e24926.answer: You should submit any relevant module that you have completed during your previous studies. Any practical project which you have received credits for will be counted if it is relevant content-wise.

c49a1ffa-cb92-4185-bfc5-a6866139fff0.question: What should I do if the application process requires more information?
c49a1ffa-cb92-4185-bfc5-a6866139fff0.answer: There will be separate forms to fill in this information in a more organized manner soon. Check back inside the application platform in around a week and apply with the provided forms.

a72ac01d-7826-4554-a47d-b8e5c9ed5c12.question: If the bachelor program of TUM Informatik only offers thesis of 15 credits, does this mean I will not be qualified for the AI in Society program, even if the content of the thesis project is qualified for the application?

6f885c68-2f8e-4d5d-9f0c-66f4c15f4052.question: What is the format of the list of the best 140 ECTS along with the proof of the practical project worth at least 18 ECTS credits completed during bachelor’s studies that I need to submit on my online application for the Master of Science - AI in Society program?
6f885c68-2f8e-4d5d-9f0c-66f4c15f4052.answer: The respective forms for the list of the best 140 ECTS and the proof of the practical project worth at least 18 ECTS credits will be provided inside the application platform in about a week.

8c16d2e1-59d9-445f-9540-0de484240e06.question: What should I do if there is no document regarding the content of the project in my university's system?
8c16d2e1-59d9-445f-9540-0de484240e06.answer: You may need to reach out to the instructor of the module and ask for an official module description.

85d86989-8b67-4afd-a13d-192108295555.question: Can I use a VPD from uni-assist from October last year for my application to the M.Sc. AI in Society program?
85d86989-8b67-4afd-a13d-192108295555.answer: If you still have a valid VPD, there is no need to get a new one. Please submit the one you already have.

8afa92e2-7d4d-4a80-a503-c95dcacd7720.question: Would I still be required to pay the standard application fee, or are there any fee waivers or reductions available for current international students?
8afa92e2-7d4d-4a80-a503-c95dcacd7720.answer: There are no particular exceptions for fees. For general information about fees for international students, refer to the TUM website.

387a1f01-f2eb-4ff7-9c9d-745a0eaaeb6c.question: Would I still be required to pay the standard application fee, or are there any fee waivers or reductions available for current international students?
